title: steamed broccoli
directions: Place broccoli spears in a 2-quart casserole.
Add water, salt and butter.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Stir all the Hi-C orange and pineapple juice together.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add ginger ale shortly before serving. Makes approximately 68, 6 ounce servings.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: In a large pan, bring milk to a boil.
Stir corn meal into boiling milk, cook until very thick, 3 to 5 minutes stirring constantly to prevent scorching.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon together.
Mix separately the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Add just before serving.

title: one pot pasta
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pasta, and bring to a boil.
Add pasta.
Cover and simmer 16 to 18 minutes.
Stir twice.
You can add favorite meats, cooked and/or vegetables when done and sprinkle with favorite cheese, if desired.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Make jello according to directions.
Cool.
Add drained pineapple.
Save the juice.
When set, make topping of Dream Whip, already made to package directions, cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat throughly and spread on jello.
Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks, lemon juice and pineapple juice until thick.
Pour over topping.
Chill until ready to use.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon in rolls (hot dog or hamburger). Wrap in foil or place close together in covered ovenware pan. Heat until cheese melts at 400° for 15 minutes.
If frozen, double time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oregon apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apple slices evenly in lightly greased 10-inch pie plate.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle on apples; set aside.
For topping, combine cooled melted butter, brown sugar, pecans and flour in bowl.
Add eggs to mixture; blend well.
Spread topping evenly over apples.
Bake for about 35 minutes or until apples are soft and topping is lightly brown.
If desired, sprinkle baked pie with powdered sugar and chopped pecans.

title: donna's pizza crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease pan; spread dough.
Let stand a few minutes.
Top with favorite pizza toppings and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush a large package or Oreos in blender.
Mix the rest in the order listed to make cream mixture.
Layer Oreos and cream mixture in flowerpot with Oreos on top.
Decorate with green coconut, candy worms and artificial flower.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese together with the vanilla. Add milk slowly, then sugar, then the Cool Whip.
Cream.
Put into a large 9-inch pie crust of graham crackers.

title: dan's homemade salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate leftovers. Serve with taco chips.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Slightly beat eggs.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Then pour cream mixture into pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes longer at 300 or until knife comes out clean inserted 1 inch from edge.
Before cutting let stand 10 minutes.
Serve in wedges.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients; add eggs, oil and vanilla, beating constantly.
Fold in nuts, raisins or dates and chopped apples.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Prepare the following topping.

title: cucumber party sandwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread on rye bread.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables in large casserole dish.
Heat Cheez Whiz and soup.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with bread crumbs, then with onion rings.
Heat in a 350° oven until center is hot.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and onion soup. Pour over chicken breasts.
Cook on 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Add pineapple and bell pepper.
Cook 15 minutes longer, uncovered.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: blueberry-banana roll
directions: Grease and flour heavily 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. In a small bowl beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar until stiff peaks form.

title: fried catfish
directions: Wash fish. Mix all other ingredients together. Pan-fry or deep-fry in hot oil until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: fruit-filled melons
directions: Cut each cantaloupe in half and remove the seeds.
Use melon baller to scoop out pulp, reserving shells.
Trim thin slice from the bottom of each shell.
In a bowl, mix 2 cups melon balls, orange, apple, peach, blueberries and strawberries.

title: greek tortellini salad
directions: In a large bowl combine cooked pasta, sweet peppers, onion and olives.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Combine brownie mix, yogurt, water and chocolate packet (if included) in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread in pan. Bake 30 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edge. Cool before cutting.

title: carrots marinade
directions: Cook carrots; drain and sliver lengthwise in bowl.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate 1 day before serving.
A sprinkle or two of celery seed really adds.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 13 x 9 pan. Cool. Punch holes in cake and pour can of Eagle Brand milk over cake. Pour caramel sauce over cake. Crush Butterfinger candy bar and sprinkle over cake. Top with Cool Whip. May garnish with more candy bar sprinkles.

title: greek chicken oregano
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut fryer into serving pieces.
Brush with oil or butter.
Place in 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water and bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, basting frequently.
Reduce heat to 50°; mix lemon juice with 1/4 cup water and pour over chicken.
Season well with salt, pepper and oregano. Dot with butter.
Bake an additional hour, basting frequently, turning over to cook evenly.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted margarine.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 cup liquid. Chop peaches and sprinkle on top of batter.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/3 cup peach juice. Pour on top of peaches.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pone spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes in flat casserole dish.

title: rich whole wheat bread
directions: Into a large mixing bowl measure the yeast and sea salt. Measure the oil and honey into a cup and stir into the dry yeast and salt.
Add the water and stir.
Mix in the milk powder.
Add the 2 cups whole wheat flour and stir until fairly smooth.
Stir in the eggs.
Add 5 cups of the remaining whole wheat flour, 2 cups at a time.
Dump another cup (no. 8) over the kneading board and scrape batter onto the board.
Knead in.
Add as much of the ninth cup as necessary to stop dough from sticking.
Knead for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Oil the ball in the bowl.
Cover with a clean, wet towel and put to rise in a very warm, draft-free place.
Finger test.
When risen, punch down and shape into 3 loaves.
(At this point, make any seed, fruit or nuts addition.)
With butter or margarine, grease three 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking pans. Put loaves into the pans.
Cover again with wet towel and put again to rise in a very warm place.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Cool on a wire rack.
Eat hot, but any left over will keep.

title: quick baked fillet
directions: Dip fish in combined ingredients, except corn flakes.
Roll in corn flakes.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven for 500° for 15 minutes.
Thaw frozen fish before dipping.
Needs no watching.
Do not cook over 15 minutes.

title: almond joy cake
directions: This cake will feed about 30 people because it is almost like eating a candy bar.

title: fruit glazed cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until just set.
Chill.
Drain fruits thoroughly.
Arrange in circle on chilled pie.
Stir marmalade and spoon over fruits to glaze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package; add margarine.
Stir until melted.
Add corn, soup and cheese.
Stir well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn muffins
directions: Grease two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Peel and cut apples into eighths, then into little pieces.
Juice the lemon; mix with some water and mix with apple pieces (to prevent discoloration).

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Bake ribs until done, then mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: banana dip crunch
directions: Cut banana in half.
Have child dip or roll banana in yogurt and then in wheat germ or cereal.
Let kids dip, roll and enjoy this healthy treat.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk slowly and heat.
Add eggs by putting a small amount of milk into egg mixture.
Stir constantly until it boils - add butter and vanilla. Put 1 sliced banana in bottom of mazola oil baked pie shell. (see pastry section).
Add small amount of cream mixture and more bananas, then cover with cream filling.
Chill several hours.
Top with real whipped cream or meringue.

title: noodle goulash
directions: Brown the ground beef in the hot fat.
Add onion and celery. Cook, stirring often, until opaque (approximately 10 minutes). Gently mix in the hot, drained noodles, cooked according to directions.
Add tomatoes, cheese, salt, pepper and chestnuts. Let slowly simmer or put in greased 2-quart casserole and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
If baking in a casserole, shred more cheese over the top.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus in boiling salted water by any preferred method.
Put in shallow 2-quart baking dish. Melt butter in saucepan and mix 2 tablespoons of crumbs.
Set aside.

title: porcupine sausage balls
directions: Melt butter in frying pan and brown onion in it.
Add chopped green pepper, tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Cook until green pepper is tender. Make the sausage into small balls and roll in the uncooked rice. Place in greased baking casserole and pour the tomato mixture over sausage balls.
Cover baking dish and bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir dry pudding mix into
Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and oleo.
Spread nuts in bottom of mini tart shells.
Pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy; add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Stir dry ingredients and add to cream mixture, stirring until well blended. Spread dough in 5 x 10-inch pan, reserving some of mixture for the top.
Spread raspberry pie filling.
Drop reserved mixture by spoonful on top of filling. Make a glaze of powdered sugar and hot water and drizzle over bars after they are done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain beef.
Add all soups, enchilada sauce, corn and oregano.
Bring to boil.
In casserole dish, put layer of meat mixture and one layer of cheese until all are used.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate raisin bread "pudding"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3-quart baking dish.
Cut bread slices in half diagonally.
Arrange in baking dish so slices overlap slightly.
In saucepan, heat milk and cocoa powder over medium-low heat until cocoa is dissolved.
Remove from heat. Stir in heavy cream, sugar, eggs and vanilla until blended. Pour mixture over bread; let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Ready to serve in 2 hours and 15 minutes when
cool.

title: crusty french bread
directions: Pour water in large bowl. Add yeast and sugar. Add salt, then add flour a little at a time and mix until smooth. Knead dough, then shape into a ball and place in a greased bowl. Grease top of dough and put wax paper or plastic wrap on top. Let rise until double, then punch down and divide into 2 balls. Let stand 5 minutes. Grease hands and shape dough into long slender loaves. Place on greased sheet. Cut diagonal slits on top. Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast quiche
directions: Heat oven 425 degrees.
Bake pie shells about 7 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350 degrees.
In medium skillet brown sausage.
Drain; reserve 2 Tbsp. fat.
Cook onions and green pepper in fat until brown and tender.
Stir in sausage.
Spoon into pie shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In medium bowl beat eggs add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese and sausage mixture.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes or until done.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first four ingredients together as listed.
Beat well. Scald milk in large saucepan.
Add egg mixture slowly to milk. Leave over heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Divide into two equal parts.
Mix pudding as directed; add one mixed package to each half with enough milk to fill freezer to fill line.
Makes two 5-quart freezers.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice until boiling.
Mix with jello.
Cool. Add buttermilk.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into dish and refrigerate.

title: mom's pizza
directions: Brown ground round.
Follow directions on pizza mix.
I put the crusts in the oven until almost cooked, take out about 10 minutes, add meats to you liking.
Add diced onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Cheese is my favorite so I pile that on.
You may use more or less to your liking.

title: impossible pie!
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan that is lightly greased. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until browned and set.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in a large kettle until tender.
Drain.
While noodles are cooking, brown and drain hamburger.
In a large pan, mix tomato paste and water together, mixing well.
Add hamburger, season packets and oregano.
Salt to taste and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In large casserole dish or baking pan, layer.
Top with sauce, then cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry easy
directions: Stir-fry and toss with different types of pasta or rice.
You may substitute or add almost any fresh or frozen vegetables you choose:
squash, mushrooms, cabbage, cauliflower, broccoli.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, half and half and salt together.
Pour over cheese.
Cover overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cauliflower carrot salad
directions: Step 1:
Combine cucumbers, broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, salad bar cheese and seasoning salt in a clean Lexan pan.
Mix well.

title: shrink-proof, weep-proof meringue
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until transparent and thickened.
(This will take about 2 minutes.)
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Continue beating while gradually pouring cooked mixture into egg whites.
Beat three minutes or until stiff (but not dry) peaks form.
Do not overbeat.
Yields enough for 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: hurry up rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt, butter or oil on top of a hot stove and bring to a boil.
Remove and let the mix get cold. Combine yeast with lukewarm water until all is melted.
Add egg to the milk mixture well.
Add milk mixture to the flour mixture; mix well.
Knead on flour board.
Make rolls or loaf; place in oiled pan.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
Rub with butter.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Bring chicken stock, onion and seasonings to boil in large pot.
Add broccoli, reduce heat to simmer and cook until soft, about 8 minutes.
In separate pan, melt butter and add flour. Whisk with wire whisk for a few minutes over medium high heat until smooth.
Slowly add milk, whisking constantly to avoid lumps.
Stir with wooden paddle as you slowly add broccoli to roux.
Whisk vigorously until soup begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and adjust seasonings.
Garnish with grated cheddar cheese.

title: beef rollettes
directions: Slice tenderloin very thin (you may also use thin sliced sandwich steaks).
Pieces should be about 4 1/2 x 3-inch.
Spread mustard on steak and put two pieces each of carrots and pickles on top.
Roll and fasten each with toothpicks.
Lightly brown in frying pan and add beef broth.
Simmer lightly until done.
Serve with mashed potatoes and tossed salad.

title: shrimp stuffed fish
directions: Heat broth, lemon juice and 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet. Arrange fish in broth mixture and simmer for 3 minutes. Place fish in a baking dish.

title: marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan or bowl on the stove or in the microwave.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine. Melt until smooth when stirred.
Immediately add cereal; stir until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: spinach salad
directions: I add sliced fresh orange and goat cheese.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Blend dry ingredients.
Mix in oil, orange rind, juice and egg.
Fold in cranberries.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly before slicing with a thin, sharp knife.
Yields 16 servings.

title: spice kitchen fragrance
directions: Mix all together and boil slowly.

title: beary cherry delight
directions: Stir all ingredients together; refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cheese salad
directions: Cook carrots in microwave for 3 minutes.
Toss with celery and cheese.
Line salad bowl with green leaves.
Add salad and decorate with sliced eggs and parsley.
Serve with an oil and vinegar dressing.

title: "more sinful than sex" chocolate dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend flour, oleo and 1 cup of nuts. Crush in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, forming a crust.
Bake crust for 20 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese with sugar.
Blend in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix package of pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with more Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the top with nuts and shaved chocolate.
Freeze before serving.

title: english tea scones
directions: Mix all ingredients except raisins with pastry cutter until mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Add raisins. Divide into 2 parts.

title: ham roll-ups(microwave)
directions: Spread mustard on each slice of ham.
Put cheese on each ham slice.
Roll short end so the cheese is enclosed.
Cut roll-ups in quarters crosswise and secure with toothpicks.
Arrange roll-ups in a single layer on plate or platter.
Heat uncovered on Full power 3 to 4 minutes until hot.
Heat remaining roll-ups.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in a large skillet. Cover and cook on medium heat 15 minutes or until desired texture.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Combine creamed mixture with dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Gently stir in carrots and pecans.
Pour into pans and bake 20 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: spinach rice
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, heat milk.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in a 325° oven and bake for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: dried beef appetizer
directions: Mix cheese, Worcestershire sauce and onion soup.
Spread a little on each piece of dried beef.
Roll up around a pickle spear.
Cut into slices.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Grate cheese in big mixing bowl. Pour cooked macaroni over cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add bell pepper and onion (sauteed), pimento, soup and mayonnaise. Mix well and bake uncovered at 400° until brown in 8 x 10-inch dish.

title: quick hamburger dish
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger meat with onion soup mix.
Add 1 can beer after meat is brown.
Then add sour cream and stir. Serve over egg noodles.

title: ham-it-up crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place one slice of ham on each rectangle.
Add horseradish to mustard (amount depends on preference).
Spread mustard mixture on ham slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Starting with shortest side, roll up each rectangle and press edges to seal.
Cut each of the 4 rolls into 5 slices, forming 20 slices in all.
Place each slice cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice florentine style
directions: Bring bouillon broth, vegetables and spices to full boil. (Vegetables may need to be chopped into smaller pieces before adding.)
Remove from heat and stir in rice.
Cover and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Fluff lightly before serving.
Serve with sliced chicken or turkey.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
simmer over a low fire 15 to 20 minutes; serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6 people

title: lemon-cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine crumbs with nuts, sugar and butter, blending well.
Press firmly on bottom of a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread according to directions and bake in 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Cool and crumble in large bowl.
Add bacon, chopped vegetables and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: berry berry dippy
directions: Blend all together and serve with fruit.

title: strawberry pudding pie
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding; beat 2 minutes.
Blend in 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Fold in quartered strawberries.
Pour in cool shell.
Chill.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and garnish with whole strawberries.

title: boiled salad dressing
directions: Mix vinegar, water, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Mix other ingredients and add to boiled mixture.
Cook until thick. Keep refrigerated.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and molasses.
Add egg.
Add seasoning.
Mix the water and evaporated milk together.
Alternate flour with liquid.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top (optional).
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Separate crescent rolls and place in ungreaesd 12-inch pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch pan. Press together and up the sides.
Seal.
Spoon sausage over the crust.
Sprinkle on potatoes and top with cheese.
(This may be prepared the night before and refrigerated.)
Beat eggs milk and seasonings together; pour onto crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Mix together jello and water in a microwave-safe, 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir, making sure gelatin is dissolved.
Add marshmallows.
Microwave on High 1 minute. Stir until smooth.
Pour in Pammed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Roll up and slice.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat; stir in water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, onion, green pepper, olives, and cheese; toss well.
Place lettuce mixture on individual salad plates.
Spoon on meat; top with corn chips.
Serves 4 to 6

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown sausage and beef in skillet; drain.
In large bowl, mix squash, meat, chopped onion, eggs, crackers, salt, pepper, sage and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: low fat dessert
directions: Crumble cake in bite size pieces.
Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
Layer cake, pudding, pineapple, bananas, pie filling and cool whip. This will make two layers.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Bring the sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil.
Pour over vegetables while hot.
Serves 12.

title: you-name-it pie
directions: Mix together and put in graham cracker crust.
Garnish with coconut.

title: capellini with calamari and shrimp(from tony's in houston, tx)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place the walnuts on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Let cool.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream egg, sugar and milk.
Add vanilla, baking powder, oil, nutmeg and flour.
Drop by level teaspoon into hot fat and fry. Allow space in fryer as they turn over when brown on one side. Cool and coat with powdered sugar.

title: nana's pizza
directions: Mix flour, yeast, and salt in a bowl set aside.
Add to the hot water:
corn syrup and oil, mix up and make sure your water mixture cools to luke warm, as to not kill your yeast.
Mix flour mixture and water mixture together until a soft dough is formed knead your dough with flour until you can roll out on pizza stone or pan, that has been sprayed with oil.
Spread pizza sauce on dough, cover with cheese then put your meat and anything else you like on top.
Cook at 400 to 450 until cheese has melted and browned and crust is done.
Enjoy.

title: tuna log
directions: Cream chili sauce and cream cheese.
Add parsley, pepper sauce and tuna.
Chill 3 hours in a bowl.
Shape into log.
Roll in parsley.
Chill.

title: miso-beer chicken
directions: Combine miso, shoyu sauce, beer and sugar.
Mix well.
Debone thighs and soak chicken several hours.
(Overnight is better.) Best cooked on a hibachi, but may be baked or broiled.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done.
Baste often while cooking (10 minutes on each side).
Sauce is enough for 10 pounds of chicken.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix oil and egg together.
Add dry ingredients to the mixture. Add 2 tablespoons more milk. Mix thoroughly. Wipe griddle with a small amount of oil.
Use medium heat and fry.
These are fluffy and delicious.

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion and celery and then add dry stuffing and water.
Combine ground beef and evaporated milk.
Take mixture of ground beef and evaporated milk; roll into 6 balls.
Pat flat on waxed paper.
Place a spoonful of stuffing on each and seal meat around.
Mix the mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup together as a sauce and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add chocolate, instant coffee and rum extract well.
Stir in flour and 1 cup chopped walnuts.

Pour into unbaked pie shell. Decorate top with 1/2 cup walnut halves or pieces. Bake in lower third of oven for 25 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Top with whipped cream or ice cream. Refrigerate.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese and spinach.
Mix well. Spread into pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut in small squares and serve.

title: almond chicken
directions: Cut up chicken, onions and green peppers.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add in next 5 ingredients.
Add oil to wok or electric frypan.
Cook green peppers and onions.
Remove from pan. Cook almonds for 1 to 2 minutes.
Put in all chicken; add sauce until thick.
Then add vegetables and almonds.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: gourmet tenderloin
directions: "Paint" the beef with Kitchen Bouquet.
Let stand for 3 to 4 hours at room temperature to seal in juices.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes for medium, 20 minutes for medium-rare, or, if you wish well done, bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.
If desired, make Special Sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well. In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon and add to mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and stir.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool before taking out of pans.

title: hubert's favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix
thoroughly
to
minutes.
Pour
into greased (may
use Pam) and floured mold and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Test for doneness before removing from oven.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; beat in other ingredients and stir until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan, buttered and floured, in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Bake chicken, debone and cut into small pieces. cook noodles, drain. Combine remaining ingredients except cheese and place in 9x13 inch casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: luncheon rolls
directions: Stir together 2 cups flour and yeast.
In a saucepan, combine milk, water, oil and sugar; heat until warm (120° to 130°).
Add liquid to flour and yeast mixture.
Beat about 2 minutes on medium speed until smooth.
Blend in eggs.
Add 1 cup flour; beat 1 minute more.
Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour, making a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth.
Return to bowl; cover.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 24.

title: beef roast
directions: Salt, pepper and flour roast.
Place in bottom of roaster with oil.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Do not turn for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Spread onion soup mix dry on top of roast.
Reduce heat to 250° to 300°.
Cover; cook until tender, about 3 hours.
Do not add water.
Makes its own juice for gravy.
Delicious.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender; cool slightly.
Add salt, sour cream and 1 cup Cheddar cheese; set aside.
Combine egg, milk, creamed corn and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Lightly mix in corn muffin mix.
Do not overmix; leave some lumps.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks and add melted margarine.
Stir in sugar and flour mixture.
Mix, then add milk and vanilla flavoring.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into an extra large (9 5/8-inch) unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° to 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until does not shake.
Place pie on a heavy cookie sheet to cook.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: mexican chili dip
directions: *You can use V-8 or any Bloody Mary mix.

title: "dolly parton" pie
directions: Blend all ingredients well and put in graham cracker crusts; makes 2 pies.
Put in freezer until ready to eat.
Can be put in 24 individual crusts.

title: nancy's pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and butter.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add milk; keep mixing constantly.
Add lemon and vanilla extract.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, egg, salt and water.
Mix with fork and fry like crepes, spreading to make thin.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran and wheat; set aside.
In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, powder and salt; stir.
Add bran and wheat to mixture.
Mix well. Add dry mixture alternately with cream mixture and buttermilk. Mix well.
Cover and store in the refrigerator.
Keeps one month. Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° preheated oven in lightly greased pans.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown ground beef in microwave on HIGH for 3 minutes. Stir. Microwave on HIGH an additional 3 minutes. Drain. Put ground beef in large bowl. Sprinkle lightly with onion powder. Stir in salsa and beans; mix well. Spoon mixture into round 10-inch pie or cake pan. Sprinkle shredded cheese over meat mixture. Place black olives on top. Microwave on MEDIUM-HIGH for 4 minutes or until cheese is melted. Eat with tortilla chips.

title: orange carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until just tender.
Drain and pour carrots in a dish.
Combine orange juice, salt, sugar and pepper in a pan and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over carrots.

title: peanut butter milkshake
directions: Stir ingredients together thoroughly, making sure that there are no clumps of peanut butter.
Dip into cup and serve.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve warm with chips or vegetables.

title: smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender; blend until smooth.
If desired, substitute any other fruit such as blueberries, etc.

title: fresh peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add mayonnaise, stirring until dissolved.
While this is cooling, peel and thinly slice peaches.
Place peaches and pineapple with juice in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour jello over fruit.
Chill until set.

title: barbecue chipotle sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 30 minutes.

title: golden orange dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Serve over fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: honey wheat spiral bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together 1 cup of the all-purpose flour and the yeast.
In a small saucepan, heat and stir milk, honey, margarine or butter and salt until warm (120° to 130°) and margarine or butter almost melts.
Add to flour mixture; add egg.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping the sides of the bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Using a spoon, stir in whole-wheat flour and as much of the remaining all-purpose flour as you can.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes total).
Shape into a ball.
Place in a lightly greased bowl; turn once to grease the surface.
Cover and let rise on a warm place until double (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift the flour once with soda and salt.
In separate bowl, cream the margarine, granulated sugar and brown sugar together. Add beaten egg and mix until smooth.
Add peanut butter; stir well, then add to flour mixture.
Mix to a stiff batter, then add vanilla.
Form into tiny balls; roll in sugar and press onto a greased cookie sheet.
Press cookie with back of a fork to make a waffle design.
Bake.
Remove from pan to cool plate immediately. These are good with milk!

title: carter's potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients in the order given in large bowl. Place in 9 x 13 greased pan (prefer glass) and top with crushed corn flakes. Bake 1 hour or until bubbling and brown. Hint: Partially thaw potatoes before mixing.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cut up fryers or chicken pieces.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 2 hours or more at 325°.
Sauce is delicious over rice.

title: nutty sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix all ingredients well (hold out 1/2
cup nuts for topping).
Pour into well-oiled Corning Ware dish.
Place
cup nuts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: calypso pie(ice cream cake)
directions: Combine Oreo and butter.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on top of Oreos.
Make chocolate syrup by melting chocolate squares and margarine.
Add sugar and Pet milk.
Cook until thick.
Spread on top of ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with peanuts.
Freeze overnight.
Set out a few minutes before serving.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Cook broth, chives and celery.
Pour egg very slowly into boiling broth, stirring to make egg into shreds.

title: "the recipe"(chocolate sauce)
directions: Place all the ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Absolutely great for ice cream, pound cake, etc.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter in large bowl.
Mix together.
Cook sugar and Milnot together until it forms a soft ball (approximately 12 minutes).
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and pour into Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix well until creamy.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add margarine, milk, peanut butter; stir.
Cook on high heat until candy thermometer reaches 230°.
Turn off fire and add vanilla. Beat mixture for about 5 minutes until mixture is thick.
Pour into greased dish. Glass works best (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).
Let cool and cut into squares.
Store in tightly closed container. Freezes very well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: celebration soup
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Add 3 cups (750 ml) of the broth; simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining broth and vegetables.
Heat to serving temperature.
Season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Yields 8 servings.
Exchange (1 cup):
1 vegetable, 1 fat.
Calories (1 cup): 62.

title: meatball parmigiana(serves 6)
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Saute onions until soft.
Add tomatoes with liquid.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer uncovered while making meatballs.
Combine 1/4 cup water, bread crumbs, meat, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and form into 24 small meatballs.
Add meatballs to sauce and simmer 15 minutes while cooking noodles.
Drain noodles. Put noodles in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with meatballs and most of sauce.
Cover with cheese slices.
Pour on rest of sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add oats and cream together.
Add the other ingredients as listed, one at a time, beating each time.
Drop about 2 inches apart on greased cookie pan and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pa. stroganoff and noodles
directions: Combine ingredients and serve over cooked noodles (wide).

title: apple bread
directions: Melt butter in baking pan (9-inch square).
In a small bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon with fork.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on melted butter in pan.
Cut apple into thin slices.
Arrange slices in rows on top of sugar mixture.
Sprinkle raisins over apples.

title: macaroni and meat sauce
directions: Cook onion, pepper and garlic in oil until tender, not browned.
Add meat and cook until brown.

title: sausage bread
directions: Spread dough out; mix egg, cheeses and sausage together. Spread on dough.
Roll like jelly roll.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and press in pie pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Combine and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle steak pieces with meat tenderizer.
Dip into flour which has been mixed with salt and pepper.
Pound with tenderizer mallet.
Put Crisco into skillet.
Place steak pieces in to brown. When steak has browned, set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, put tomatoes and chopped onions.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste. Bring to boil.
Turn down heat; simmer.
Put browned steak pieces in roasting pan or double boiler.
Pour tomato and onion mixture over steak.
Put into 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Place cloves in cheesecloth and tie with a string to side of pot.
Mix remainder of the ingredients in pot; bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot and enjoy!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and mix with soup, mushrooms, almonds, Worcestershire sauce and onion salt.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly (30 to 35 minutes).
Remove from oven and top with onions.
Return to oven just long enough for the onions to brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish.
Cook onions, green peppers and meat until meat loses red color.
Spoon off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread meat mixture in baking dish.
Cover with soup and top with a single layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly in center.
Everybody loves this!

title: lane cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350°. Makes 5 layers.

title: micky's brownies
directions: Beat all ingredients together for about 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and/or nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 300°, for about 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting and removing from pan.

title: oven baked potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a large open roasting pan (17 1/4 x 11 1/2-inch) with cooking spray.
Add butter or margarine. Place pan in oven to melt butter.
Cut unpeeled potatoes lengthwise into 8 wedges each.
Add potatoes to melted butter in pan.
Sprinkle with minced onion, salt and pepper.
Gently toss to coat.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes until potatoes are tender and evenly browned, turning occasionally.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Butter the outside of the bread.
Put mayonnaise on the inside of the bread.
Lay sliced cheese over the mayonnaise. Salt the cheese a little bit.
Put the sandwich together, butter side out, and grill on both sides.

title: all american ham and cheese salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine potatoes with enough water to cover.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Cook about 10 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Add green beans; cook 5 minutes longer or until beans are tender-crisp.
Drain; remove potatoes and cool.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Mix margarine and mayonnaise together. Add rest of ingredients and spread on bread. Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jessica's goulash
directions: Make ground beef into patties about the size of half dollars. Place in skillet with onion; cook until meat is done.
Drain well. Add tomato juice, macaroni, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: venison sauce pequante
directions: Wash venison.
Season and fry in bacon drippings and remove. Make roux with olive oil and flour.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add all seasoning, except garlic.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add venison to soup and seasoning.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add water and garlic.
Cook for 4 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves approximately 16 people.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Put the cheese through a meat grinder; set aside with butter to get soft.
To this, add dry ingredients and work well with your hands.
Put into cheese gun and squirt out on tins.
Bake in oven until they dry out.
Do not brown.
Serve piping hot.

title: chicken stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Add curry powder.
Roll beef in mixture.
Brown in small amount of olive oil.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir and add enough water to barely cover.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Boil broccoli until tender; drain and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream until well blended.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Cover well with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° the first 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for another 35 minutes, until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Add whipped topping when you serve.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Stir all together.
Put in freezer and stir once every hour for 3 to 4 hours.
Let freeze 24 hours before using.
Thaw to slush consistency.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese, margarine and Cool Whip; set aside. Mix vanilla pudding and milk, then mix all together.
Put cookie crumbs on, then some filling, then some filling, then cookie crumbs on top.
Place gummy worms on top.
Kids love this part.

title: percolator punch(24 to 30 cup percolator)
directions: Put apple cider, brown sugar, orange juice, lemonade and water in percolator.

title: mayonnaise
directions: *Or 12 tablespoons vinegar.

title: deep-fried chicken
directions: You also need a turkey fryer.

title: range rider bread
directions: Bring water and raisins to boil.
Set aside to cool; add soda. Cream sugar, butter, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix with raisin mixture.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Fill greased loaf pan 1/2 full and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in cold water for 3 to 5 minutes; drain well. Mix soup, milk and mayonnaise and heat, stirring, until smooth. Melt margarine in baking dish; blend in 1 1/2 cups of corn flake crumbs.
Place cabbage over corn flakes and pour soup mixture over cabbage.
Cover with remaining corn flakes and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: sauce o' gold
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Baste meat during last half of cooking time. Just before serving, top with remaining sauce.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions and place in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken.
Make the next layer with the cooked broccoli, then mix together the soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread mixture over the top, making sure entire area, including edges, is covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve at once.

title: mother greer's applesauce pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, mayonnaise, cheese and 3/4 sleeve Ritz crackers in baking dish.
Crumble remaining crackers on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: angel food poppy seed cake
directions: Empty contents of angel food cake mix into mixing bowl.
Add egg whites, poppy seed and water and bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: lemon-lime chiffon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix together gingersnap crumbs, melted butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and up sides of prepared pan.
Bake crust until slightly darkened, 9 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon of pineapple liquid.
Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and eggs.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and allspice.
Add to zucchini mixture. Blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 60 - 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove.

title: salsa
directions: Drain juice from whole tomatoes into blender or food processor. Put in peppers, chili powder, crushed red peppers and garlic powder.
Use stir button, then put the tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes in and hit stir button again, 5 to 10 seconds.
Try not to mix too much.
Your own taste will decide the amount of spices and peppers. The salsa tastes better if it's chunkier, so watch the blending time.

title: meringue torte
directions: Separate eggs; put whites in small mixer bowl, yolks in large bowl.
Grease and dust with flour 2 (8-inch) layer cake pans.
Set oven at 350° to preheat.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 cup sugar and shortening to the yolks in large bowl.
Beat on No. 7 speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl as necessary.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Beat on No. 1 speed until flour is dampened, then on No. 4 speed for 1 1/2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Turn into pans.
Wash and dry beaters. Beat egg whites and the 1/2 teaspoon vanilla on No. 12 speed until moist peaks form, 1/2 minute, then beat in remaining sugar gradually, beating until stiff, 1 minute longer.
Spread over cake batter, bringing against edge of pan all around.
Sprinkle with the chopped nuts.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add baking powder to cracker crumbs.
Alternate milk and crumbs.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pour juice of pineapple over layer before icing.

title: beans and meatballs(this is an easy casserole)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
With wet hands, form into 16 meatballs.
Brown in large skillet along with onions.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add beans, catsup and mustard. Cover and heat for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pizza whirls
directions: Mix together and spread on party rye slices.
Cook in 300° or 350° oven for 10 minutes or until crust is bubbly.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground round and garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano; simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse with hot water.

In a big buttered pan, arrange alternate layers of noodles, thin spread of Ricotta, tomato-meat sauce, Mozzarella slices, Parmesan cheese and finishing with a layer of the meat sauce and the Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cover; refrigerate.
Before serving, reheat 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: easy beef bake
directions: Mix soups and ginger ale.
Stir in meat.
Place in covered casserole and bake covered at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: georgia's fudge pie
directions: Mix together and pur into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set around the edge.

title: black bean and shrimp in sauce
directions: In large skillet over high heat, cook onion and celery for 5 minutes in 2 teaspoons hot oil.
Add chili powder and cook one minute.
Add tomatoes with liquid, salt, oregano and red pepper flakes to taste.
Heat to boiling, stirring to break tomatoes. Simmer 10 minutes at reduced heat, uncovered, stirring once in a while.

title: ginger sparkplug carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Put in buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix lemon juice and seasonings; pour over carrots.
Dot with margarine.
Cover and bake in hot oven (400°) for 1 hour, or until carrots are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cheese danish
directions: Place 10 biscuits on a parchment-lined cookie sheet, leaving a one-inch space between each one.
Roll out dough to flatten making sure that there remains a space between each one. Mix cream cheese and vanilla together.
Spread evenly on each biscuit. Place one slice of apple on top; drizzle about 1 teaspoon caramel topping over apple slice and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients; allow to chill until cold.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir apples and orange juice in a large bowl.
Combine light brown sugar, white sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Stir with apples until coated.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Moisten pastry edge with water and prepare top crust.
Bake until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Chop pepper and drain off juice very well.
Boil pepper, sugar and vinegar for 6 minutes.
Add Sure-Jell; boil 3 more minutes. Pour into jars and seal.
To serve, spread cream cheese on Ritz crackers and a drop of pepper jelly.
Very good.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken, onion and egg in a large greased casserole dish. Mix soups, broth and canned vegetables and pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Mix milk, mayonnaise and flour; spread evenly over soup mixture for crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until crust is brown.

title: chatham chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Place chipped beef in 10 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken on top of beef. Mix together the sour cream, soup and cream cheese. Pour over beef and chicken. Sprinkle parsley on top. Bake for 2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a bowl combine eggs and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, onions, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Pat mixture in an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon off excess fat.

title: easy vanilla sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Cover and process at blend until smooth.
Then serve as a hot sauce.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream
sugar and salad oil.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour and soda.
Mix in apples.
Pour into lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour, or until done.

title: dressing
directions: Precook celery and onion until soft and mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° with your turkey.

title: sour cream and raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs, 1 cup sour cream, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg until well blended.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in center of oven at 375° for 40 minutes or just until set.
Cool.
If desired, top pie with remaining 1/2 cup sour cream; smooth over entire top and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: make-up(for halloween)
directions: Mix ingredients together like paste.
Add colorings.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in order listed.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter over top; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with whipped topping.
This can be frozen.

title: chicken salad log
directions: Mix cream cheese, salad dressing, lemon juice, salt, ginger, pepper and pepper sauce.
Stir in chicken, eggs and 1/4 cup green onions.
Shape into log, 8 x 2-inches.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut bell pepper rings to make strips.
Place strips diagonally across log, dividing log into 4 sections. Sprinkle sesame seed on one section.
Repeat with
3 tablespoons onion, the olives and pimiento on remaining sections.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: coq au vin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken.
Rub it with salt, pepper and flour.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides and arrange in deep casserole dish.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to fat in skillet.
Gradually stir in wine, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Add onions, garlic, parsley and bay leaves. Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, covered for 1 hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Stir in beer.
Spray bread pan with Pam, then pour 2 tablespoons melted butter in the bottom.
Add the bread batter alternating with small amounts of butter.
Pour remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn out and eat immediately.

title: delicious taco dip
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain grease.
Add taco mix and chilies. In large casserole, layer beans, meat, cheese and taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Serve with dollops of sour cream, chopped black olives or scoops of guacamole after baking.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; let simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Dice a few slices of bacon and brown with onion in frying pan. Drain.
Add flour, sugar, catsup and mustard.
Mix thoroughly. Combine with beans and put in baking dish.
Put strips of bacon on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Mix together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time to butter mixture, then add the flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: garlic croutons for salads
directions: Spread margarine over both sides of bread slices.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cut slices into 3/4-inch cubes.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until croutons are crisp and dry.
Let cool completely.
Store in airtight container. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: gouda pastry
directions: Thaw 2 pastry shells.
Roll into circles.
Wrap Gouda into circles.
Pinch and seal with water.
Slit holes in top.
Brush top with egg and water mixture.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 450°, for 15 minutes at 375° and then set for 45 minutes.

title: turkey burger or meat loaf
directions: Crumble bread into milk.
Beat egg; add to mixture.
In a bowl, mix shoyu and sugar.
Mix meat, bread mixture and shoyu together. For meat loaf, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For hamburger, grill.

title: maryann's pasta salad
directions: Add all ingredients to drained cooked linguini.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: tahitian spareribs
directions: Place ribs on a rack in a roasting pan; bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
all
dry
ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: saucy apricot chicken
directions: Put chicken in slow cooker.
Combine preserves and soup mix; spoon over chicken.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 5 hours until tender. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in small chunks in large mixing bowl. Add chopped vegetables
and
mix
well.
Add salad dressing, a little more may be
needed
if
consistency
is
too dry.
Add eggs, bacon bits, salt and pepper to taste.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high until hot, then turn to low and cook until done, 4 to 6 hours.

title: cherry salad
directions: Make Jell-O using 1/2 water called for.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Let congeal.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. In a large bowl, cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Blend well. Gradually add sifted ingredients, mixing well after each addition. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes or until done. Let cool on wire rack.

title: ohio cheesecake
directions: Stir together crumbs, oleo and nuts.
Press into bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: green tomato and vidalia onion tart
directions: Bake pastry shell 6 to 8 minutes or until golden. Cook onions, covered in small amount of boiling water, 5 minutes or until tender. Drain and arrange cooked onions on bottom of pastry. Arrange tomato slices atop onions. Sprinkle with chives, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Spread on top of pie and bake at 375°, uncovered, until golden and bubbly.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail and syrup, 1 cup coconut and the eggs in large bowl.
Blend at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken. Debone, if necessary.
Mix soup and chicken. Place in casserole dish.
Pour butter, Ritz crackers, poppy seed and sour cream mixture over chicken.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine and then add everything else except crumbs.
Separate rolls into rectangles; mash out small lines.
Put mix in center; pull dough to top and twist.
Brush with margarine; dip squares in crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: western baked beans
directions: Mix all together and cook in oven at 400° for about 45 minutes or until ingredients are done.
Great for large get togethers.

title: hungry man meal
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet and drain off fat.
Layer in casserole dish the hamburger and sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over potatoes and hamburger.
Pour cream of mushroom soup and milk over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle paprika over steak and brown in skillet in butter. Add garlic and broth and simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Add pepper; cover and cook 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce and add to meat mixture. Blend until smooth. Heat through. Serve over rice.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Add pudding to pumpkin and other ingredients on pumpkin can. Omit sugar.
Follow directions on can.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli and chopped onion in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper and pat of butter.
Microwave 8 minutes.
Stir, microwave 8 more minutes.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Let set for 5 minutes and add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until ingredients are well mixed.
Add to drained broccoli and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and put in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together, sift if lumpy.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Spread in buttered 8-inch pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast and nutmeg in large bowl.
Heat milk, sugar and oil until warm.
Add to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Add egg.
Mix in remaining flour.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into an 8 x 8 pan. Bake 15-20 minutes in 350° oven. While crust is baking, mix together next 4 ingredients and pour on hot baked crust. Bake 20 minutes more. When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into bars when cool.

title: poor man's icing
directions: Mix first two ingredients until smooth and heat until thick and forms a ball.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with beater, then add flour and milk mixture.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Double for layer cake.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan and stir in flour; salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk, stirring continuously until sauce thickens.
Remove pan from heat and stir in the egg yolk.
Stir in the cheese.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: ham dogs
directions: Combine thoroughly salad dressing, chili sauce and sugar. Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Spread mixture on buns.
Wrap each in foil.
Heat in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Yields 8 buns.

title: lime jelly
directions: Grate rind from enough limes to measure 2 tablespoons.
Set aside.
Squeeze juice from enough limes to measure 3/4 cup.
Pour through a wire mesh strainer, discarding seeds and pulp.
Combine rind, juice and water in a 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugar.
Bring to a full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Add 1 to 2 drops food coloring, if desired.
Quickly stir in fruit pectin.
Return to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with a metal spoon. Quickly pour jelly into hot, sterilized jars, filling to 1/4-inch from top.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover immediately with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process jars in boiling water bath for 5 minutes. Cool on wire racks.
Yields 5 half-pints.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter in mixer bowl.
Add eggs; beat for 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and vanilla; mix well.
Beat in evaporated milk and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Gradually beat into pumpkin mixture.
Spread evenly into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Frost with Maple Frosting.

title: easy peach fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup softened butter. Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter whole or chopped pecans on crust. Boil together 2/3 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar for 30 seconds to 1 minute; pour over pecans and crust.

title: mama stella's tea cakes
directions: Add enough sifted flour (not self-rising) to make soft dough. Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350°.
Do not cook real brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a double boiler.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup coconut; cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Cover with meringue.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart casserole.
In medium bowl, mix flour and sugar.
Add milk slowly.
Pour batter into margarine. Dump in blueberries.
Don't stir!
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix 1 cup mashed berries, sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened and clear.
Add whole berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: party biscuits
directions: Combine butter and sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons into greased miniature muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 36 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Make paste of cocoa and coloring; add to mixture.
Add salt to flour and sift.
Add this, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat.
Put soda in vinegar.
Lightly fold in (this foams up).
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, icing with French Creme Icing.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine milk, sugar, vinegar, eggs, butter, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and dry mustard in 1-quart glass bowl.
Microwave until thick.
Stir often.
Cool.
Add 1/4 cup salad dressing or more to your liking.
Add 1/4 cup chopped onion.
Thin with milk, if you wish.
Add to cooked, diced potatoes; chill.
This is enough for about 7 medium cooked potatoes and 3 hard-cooked eggs.

title: butterscotch lace cookies
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Pour mixture over rolled oats. Let stand at room temperature overnight or 8 hours so oats absorb butter.
Heat oven to 375°.
Add remaining ingredients (flour, egg, salt, vanilla); mix well.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, vanilla and salt. Mix well with electric mixer or wire whisk.
Gradually add sugar. Chill 15 minutes.
Shape into balls with hands lightly dusted with powdered sugar.
Coat with chocolate.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: joeley's bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water in saucepan. Remove from heat. Stir in stuffing. Add remaining ingredients (except bacon).
Chill 1 hour. Roll or shape into balls.
Wrap bacon pieces around dressing balls.
Place on aluminum foil lined shallow baking pan with bacon touching foil.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, turning once.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or
12 cup Bundt pan.
Beat butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend
in
vanilla;
sift
together
flour and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out onto wire rack and cool completely.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine egg, Ricotta and Parmesan. Spread mixture on each noodle.
Roll each up.
Spread sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange rolls, seam side down. Pour remaining sauce over all.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over top. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat sauce for texas hot dogs
directions: Mash the hamburger and the chopped onion in the water in pan until fine.
Keep stirring until mixture boils; add tomato juice, ketchup, salt and sugar.
Add chili powder and red pepper to suit your taste.
Boil mixture until thick.
Stir to prevent sticking.

title: nature's spices
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
Use as desired. Especially good on meats and salads.

title: pecan crusted artichoke dip
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add spinach.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Stir in artichokes, softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, cheeses and hot pepper sauce.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2 qt casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
Top with pecans.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Meanwhile, split 6 pitas horizontally.
Cut each half into 6 wedges.
Arrange in single layer on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 6 - 10 minutes. Serve warm with dip.
Makes 4 c dip, 72 pita dippers.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on baking sheet.
Bake according to package directions.
While crust is baking, cream Miracle Whip, dry Ranch dressing and softened cream cheese in a bowl.
Spread creamed cheese mixture on warm crust.
Press vegetable and cheese mixture firmly onto cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Mix together flour, sugar, Crisco oil, cinnamon, egg yolks, pineapple, juice and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease tube pan and flour.
Place in cold oven and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
After cake is cool, pour on running icing.

title: swedish dreams
directions: Beat butter, sugar and rest of ingredients and bake at 300° to 325° for 15 minutes on lightly greased pan.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the first 4 ingredients.
Continue to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add last 4 ingredients and mix with a wooden spoon.
Quickly drop on wax paper by spoonfuls. Cool.
Remove from wax paper by lifting edge of paper from counter.

title: sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Wrap in foil in buns.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Refrigerate overnight or 4 to 5 hours.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Pare potatoes.
In saucepan, heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Cover; cook 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain; set aside.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix and microwave sugar and syrup 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and microwave 3 minutes.
Add vanilla, butter; mix and microwave 1 minute.
Mix in baking soda.

title: zesty sausage appetizer
directions: In medium saucepan (sprayed with cooking spray), combine apricot preserves and mustard.
Stir and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add sausage and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot from chafing dish or electric skillet.
Spear with picks. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Stir all ingredients over medium heat until hot and red hots melt.
Serve hot or cold.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine drained shrimp, cream cheese, lemon juice, dry mustard, garlic powder, onion powder and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl of electric mixer.
Blend.
(Mixer will cut up shrimp.) Add reserved shrimp juice until desired consistency is obtained. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie shell(s). Chill.
Makes 2 or 3 pies.

title: perfect apple dumplings
directions: Sauce:
Combine first four ingredients, cook 5 minutes.
Add butter.

title: dave's cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in a large bowl.
Mix milk and slaw dressing. Pour over the cabbage and carrots; mix well. Refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Will need a rectangle size cake pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread mix.
Drain corn and add to mixture.
Set aside. Brown ground beef and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1/2 of corn bread mixture in casserole dish on top of mixture; add hamburger meat, cheese and peppers.
Pour remaining corn bread mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve in a salad bowl, on a platter, or individually.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine as listed.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Combine chicken and milk in large bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Combine milk, crumbs, cheese, sesame seed, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg and coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place, skin side up, in baking pan and drizzle with olive oil.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring to boil, cook 20 minutes over low heat; stir often. Beat 1 egg yolk with 2 tablespoons milk, very slowly add to hot rice, stirring rapidly.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm or cold. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in pineapple juice and beaten eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Bring water, salt and oil to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Cook until done, 10 to 12 minutes. Drain and rinse with water and drain.
Cool to room temperature. Combine macaroni and egg mixture.
Add oranges, pineapple, coconut, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until chilled in an airtight container.
May also add cherries.

title: danish bars
directions: Boil 2 sticks margarine, sugar, egg and 1/2 cup milk for 1 minute. Take off heat and add pecans, coconut and crushed graham crackers.

title: knox blocks(kids treat! - great for summer)
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together until dissolved.
Add whipped cream.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients with 4 cups flour.
Stir in remaining flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shape and let rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with salad dressing.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend.
Stir in bananas, nuts and cherries.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Batter will be thick.
Heavily butter small tube pan and flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes in pan, then put on rack.
Freezes well.
Can double or triple recipe.
Can bake in coffee cans or vegetable cans for gift giving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients, except cucumbers and onions, to boil. Then add cucumbers and onions; bring to boil again.
Or, pour boiling solution over cold cucumbers and onions.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Stir in dry jello.
Stir well. Chill until partly set.
Stir in buttermilk.
Refrigerate until set.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.

title: easy potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing. Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with chives.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix and roll by teaspoon.
Press with thumb, making a print and fill with favorite jelly, Hershey's Kisses, M & M's, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Add Karo syrup, melted butter, salt and
vanilla.
Put	pecans in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour pie mixture
over
pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes. You can divide this mixture into 2 shallow pie crusts or use 1 deep dish pie crust.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Drain hearts; reserve liquid.
Combine all ingredients including liquid.
Mixture may appear wet.
Refrigerate until firm, overnight or for several hours.
Shape into balls.
Roll in Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Cook macaroni and add remaining ingredients.
Mix with mayonnaise mixture and refrigerate.

title: chicken potato delight
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, milk, chicken and half of cheese. Spread 3/4 of the mixture in a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle hash browns over the top and press down lightly. Spread with the remaining mix. Sprinkle with onions, potato chips and remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly. Let cool before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin strips (trim off fat).
Brown meat and mushrooms in butter.
Add onion.
Combine soup, sauce and seasonings.
Add to meat mixture.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
(Cool first.)
Serve with noodles (2 packages).

title: cajun chicken salad
directions: Dredge chicken breasts in seasoning.
Grill or pan-fry until done. Slice into thin strips.
Mix salad ingredients and top with warm chicken.
Top with dressing.
Try poppy seed and serve.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add onions and brown.
Add in flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt and heat.
Add in mushrooms and heat.
Add soup and heat for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream; heat and serve over noodles.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Take first 3 ingredients and mix until clings together.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and lemon juice; add rest of ingredients.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot.
Cut for serving after cooled.

title: m&m's party cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients gradually and 1 1/2 cups of candies (save the rest to decorate tops of cookies).
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Place a few M&M's on top of cookies.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: mexican style salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl. Toss gently. Serve immediately.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Boil water and vinegar.
Take off heat.
Mix together egg, mustard, milk, sugar, salt and flour.
Pour into water and vinegar mixture, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat and add butter; when cool, add mayonnaise.
Pour over macaroni or potatoes.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: quick chocolate truffles
directions: Gradually mix confectioners sugar into cream cheese.
Melt chocolate bits in a double boiler or microwave.
Stir the melted chocolate into the cream cheese mixture and add vanilla extract. Roll into small balls and coat half the truffles in cocoa and the other half in chocolate sprinkles.
Chill before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix this together and pour in unbaked pie shell.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Serve with carrots, celery, cauliflower, broccoli and radishes.
Best if made one day ahead.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat until it has the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Pour out on waxed paper and knead for a short while. Keep in plastic bag, taking out only as much as is needed.
