Food coloring can be added for color.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Makes 7 or 8 pancakes.

title: cookies n cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 or 8-inch round cake pans.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients except crushed cookies at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed. Gently stir in 1 cup coarsely crushed cookies. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: cavatini
directions: Boil 4 ounces shell macaroni; brown sausage and drain.
Add Ragu.
Starting with macaroni, layer in baking dish.
Pour in meat mixture, pepperoni, mushrooms and top with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 20 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate chip delight
directions: Spread a layer of Cool Whip in bottom of dish.
Dip cookies, one at a time, in milk; layer over Cool Whip.
Alternate cookies and Cool Whip, ending with a layer of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. Best when served after 6 to 8 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except ketchup. Spread mixture in a loaf pan, or shape into loaf in a rectangular pan.
Spoon ketchup over top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chicken divine
directions: Chop dried beef.
Wrap chicken and dried beef with bacon. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over wrapped chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: um good!
directions: Line pan with saltine crackers.
Melt butter and sugar.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes. Pour chocolate chips and peanut butter chips on top.
When melted, swirl.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk and marshmallows, in a large pan.
Heat Pet milk in double boiler.
Drop marshmallows in a few at a time.
When all marshmallows are melted, pour hot creamy mixture over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pack mixture into tube or Bundt pan lined with waxed paper.
Cover with waxed paper.
Use hand to press down smoothly and thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Turn out onto favorite cake plate. Decorate with halves of pecans and candied cherries.
Keep in refrigerator.
Additional fruit and nuts may be used, if desired.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: soda biscuits(1913)
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add buttermilk and shortening.
Make a soft dough.
Cook in hot oven.

title: sweet and tangy strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and spread over cake.

title: creole scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat the margarine in a skillet and lightly saute peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put a layer of half the bread cubes in the bottom, then a layer of tomatoes and a layer of sauteed mixture.
Sprinkle tomatoes with sugar, salt, paprika and dot with margarine.
Repeat layer.
Top with bread cubes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until well browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Mix milk, butter, vanilla and eggs with mixer.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Mix by hand brown sugar, flour, oleo and chopped pecans (topping).
Sprinkle topping over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, breaking up potatoes with spoon, if necessary.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in blender; chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: microwave caramel sauce
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, blend butter, brown sugar, milk and corn syrup.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring every minute.
Add vanilla extract and salt; stir to blend.
Serve warm or cold. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Peel and slice each potato fairly thin.
Layer pieces in well buttered baking dish, 3 or 4 layers.
Between each layer, sprinkle liberally with garlic salt and dot with lots of margarine.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Grated cheese can be added to the potatoes about 5 minutes before end of cooking time if desired.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Spread half of the vanilla wafers in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Cream the butter.
Add sugar and eggs; beat until smooth.
Spread on top of wafer crumbs.
Add strawberries; sprinkle nuts on top. Add remaining wafers.
Spread with whipped cream.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.
Quite a tasty treat!

title: quick barbecues
directions: Mix and cook slow for about 20 minutes.
Serve on round buns.

title: oreo hot fudge sundae
directions: Combine Oreos with 1/4 cup melted butter and press in 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze 15 minutes.
Set ice cream at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Slice ice cream into 6 pieces and place on crust. Freeze for 30 minutes.
In a saucepan, melt chocolate bar, evaporated milk, 1/2 cup butter, sugar and salt.
Boil for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla and cool.
Pour chocolate mixture over ice cream; top with nuts.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip on top; garnish with nuts and freeze.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Spread rice evenly in bottom of well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of onion soup mix.
Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix and pepper. Combine soups and water.
Blend well and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey sandwich
directions: This recipe serves a large number of people.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Let cool and add buttermilk.
Beat until well mixed and fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Mix well and pour into mold or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Cook in oil or margarine (use your judgment about how much) until tender, not too brown or overcooked.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare brownie mix as directed. Spread into well greased 9x13 inch baking pan. In small mixing bowl, beat cheese, margarine, cornstarch

till fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk, egg and vanilla till smooth. Pour evenly over brownie batter. Bake 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Cool. Spread with frosting if desired. Cut into squares. Makes 36 to 40 brownies.

title: nut bars
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter together; then add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken strata
directions: Dice
2 slices buttered bread and set to one side.
Cut 6 slices
into cubes and spread in a buttered casserole dish. Spread chicken
over
bread
cubes.
Mix	onion,	celery	and mayonnaise together and spread on chicken.
Mix eggs, milk and soup;
pour over chicken.
Top with buttered bread cubes.
Let stand 1	hour. Bake
hour
at
Sprinkle with grated cheese and
bake 10	more
minutes.	Let
stand a few minutes before serving.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, Parmesan cheese, parsley, baking powder and salt.
Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
These are like the biscuits at Red Lobster!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt oleo in microwave at 100% power for 30 to 40 seconds and combine with pretzels.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and microwave, uncovered, at 70% to 80% power for 2 to 4 minutes.
Set aside and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, topping and powdered sugar and spread over crust.
Place in refrigerator to partially set.
In an 8-cup container, heat 2 cups of water and add gelatin.
Heat an additional minute or two at 100% power until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add strawberries and pineapple and refrigerate until partially set.
Pour on top of other two layers and refrigerate until very firm.

title: chicken and biscuit casserole
directions: Melt oleo, add flour, broth, sweet milk, eggs (cut up).
Cook (until pretty thick).
Line bottom of casserole dish with cut up chicken.
Pour over the first mixture.
Split biscuits.
Put on top.
Cook in oven until biscuits are brown at 350°.

title: great bean casserole
directions: Saute chuck and onion well.
Mix well with the other ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Cover with Fritos and Longhorn cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (double for a large casserole).

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Dot with your choice of margarine.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over chicken.
Sprinkle oregano over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed ground beef rolls
directions: In a bowl, blend ground beef, egg, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and water; mixture will be quite moist.
Cut a strip of waxed paper, 20 inches long.
Moisten top side.
Form a 4-inch wide strip of meat mixture the length of waxed paper.
Cut cream cheese into 8 sticks.
Place sticks along the length of the ground beef. Pick up waxed paper to help lift the meat over the filling.
Form a lengthwise roll; cut into 8 pieces crosswise.
Dust each piece with flour on all sides.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rub butter over pie shell.
Fry bacon crisp, then crumble.
Combine eggs, cream, Tabasco, salt, nutmeg, sugar, cayenne and pepper with hand beater.
Beat enough to stir thoroughly.
Sprinkle bacon and grated cheese with pie shell. Pour in cream mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and reduce heat to 300° and bake 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand about 15 minutes before cutting. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine, just until it is completely melted.
Remove from heat; add sugar and egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Then add chocolate chips. Mix until distributed throughout batter.
Pour in greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with foil for 1/2 hour.
This keeps brownies moist.
Cut and store in airtight container.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Layer seasoned vegetables in casserole dish.
Cover with meat and beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break or cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces (about nickel-size).
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: spaghetti with string beans, clams and vodka
directions: *A 16-ounce can of cut green string beans can be used, but, of course, fresh green beans give a better flavor.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes for 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain and mash. Butter a 2-quart casserole and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat cheese and eggs with electric mixer at high speed until almost smooth.
Add sour cream, scallions, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat at low speed until combined.
Stir in the mashed potatoes and put mixture in prepared casserole.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter; add eggs and oil.
Blend well.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda and add gradually to 1st mixture. Drop by teaspoon ball onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Really good.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken.
Then cube in small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Saute onions and bell peppers in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in buttered casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked zucchini dish
directions: Beat 4 eggs until thick and add to ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 5 tortillas on greased baking sheets. Sprinkle each with 1/4 c. cheese. Place remaining tortillas on top of cheese.
Cook chicken in 1 Tbsp. oil until no longer pink. Add 2 Tbsp. taco seasoning and 1 Tbsp. water. Mix well, remove from heat.
Combine refried beans, rest of seasoning mix and 1 Tbsp. water in a small bowl.
Spread about 1/4 c. bean mixture on each tortilla, layer with a drizzle of taco sauce, chicken mixture, remaining cheese, and toppings. Bake 5-8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese strata(prize winning recipe of lorraine pauley)
directions: Trim crusts from bread; cut 12 "doughnuts" and holes from slices.
Use bread scraps to line bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased casserole.
Put cheese over bread.
Add layer of broccoli, then layer of ham.
Put "doughnuts" and holes on top.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard, onion and salt and pour over casserole. Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a slow oven at 325° for 55 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle with shredded cheese 5 minutes before baking time ends.

title: vegetable sunburst
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan cook carrots in boiling water to cover just until tender-crisp.
Place hot carrots under cold running water until cool enough to handle; drain.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese.
Pour in corn and peppers (drain corn).
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbling.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix to a soft dough with eggs, milk and melted shortening.
Cut out.
Deep fry; drain and sprinkle with white sugar or put in bag with powdered sugar and shake gently.

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, water and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts; stir occasionally.
Add tuna, pimento, parsley and spaghetti. Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown beef with onion in large skillet, stirring to crumble. Drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Place in a 400° oven to keep hot.
Prepare batter; beat with mixer, eggs, milk and oil.
Add salt and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over pizza filling; cover filling completely. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until puffed and golden brown.

title: sweet potato and apple dish
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Fry apples in 2 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Place sweet potatoes, then apple slices in a casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of maple syrup mixture over them.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven and baste with remaining syrup.
Return to oven and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Keep a check on them so they do not overcook.

title: holiday morning french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon (or to taste) cinnamon in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add apples.
Toss to coat well.
Spread apple mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish. Arrange slices of bread on top.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and remaining 2 teaspoons (or to taste) cinnamon until well blended. Pour mixture over bread, soaking bread completely.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.

title: southern comfort cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except walnuts; beat at medium speed for two minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour.
Set on rack to cool. Invert on serving plate.
Brush top and sides of cake with glaze.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream together the oleo and powdered sugar with hands. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven. Don't let bottom brown. Roll in powdered sugar while hot and cool on wax paper.

title: apple pie filling(for canning)
directions: In large saucepan blend first four ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add lemon juice.
Pack apples into 7-quart jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Fill with hot syrup leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 20 minutes.
Line pan with pastry.
Add 1 quart pie filling.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Fry meat until done.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients together; add a little water.
(You can rinse out each can with the water.)
Heat in oven until good and hot at 250° to 350°, about 15 minutes.
Cover lightly if the egg noodles get crusty.

With tongs,

Cook 1 to 3 minutes, until golden brown. Serve immediately with vanilla ice cream.

title: supreme salad
directions: Place all ingredients, except the jello, in a bowl and mix or toss.
Sprinkle dry jello over this mixture and stir until well blended in.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Fry bacon; add to hamburger and onions.
Put in casserole with beans.
Add sugar and dry mustard to catsup or chili sauce and vanilla, then put on top of casserole.
You can top this with either Mozzarella or Monterey cheese, your choice.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand a while before serving.

title: dressing
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well, with enough broth to make mixture look soupy.
Put in baking pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 7x11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon salt and water.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and flavoring well.
Stir dry ingredients and blend into shortening mixture.
Chill for one hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into small stars.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Put two cookies together with melted chocolate.
Decorate, if desired.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add salt, vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Blend together.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop mixture on cookie sheet covered with foil.
Place in oven and turn heat off.
Leave overnight.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
May be made early in the day for dinner.

title: tabasco cheese wafers
directions: Add Tabasco to butter; cream well.
Blend in cheese and flour. Form mixture into roll; wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices; place on waxed paper lined baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn-crispy fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Mix corn flakes, flour, salt, paprika and pepper in paper bag.
Dip chicken pieces in evaporated milk; shake with corn flake mixture until coated.
Melt butter in baking pan.
Place chicken skin side down in melted butter.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: macaroni and cheddar bake
directions: Brown the meat and onion. Combine rest of the ingredients and add to the prepared macaroni, cheese and the beef.
Put in 2-quart casserole and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: sue's perfect peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches on bottom of oblong baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg, tossing with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches and drizzle with butter. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cinnamon and ice cream, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Boil the raisins in the water until half of the water is left. Mix the flour and sugar well.
Combine the sour cream, egg yolks, vanilla, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well.
Add the sugar, flour, raisins and water.
Bring to full boil.
Add 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Put in baked pie shell.
With egg whites, make a meringue.
Spread on pie and brown to a golden brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Start browning sausage; drain fat.
In 8 x 8 square pan, cut and press biscuits to form crust. In mixing bowl, beat eggs with milk. When sausage is ready, drain fat and spread onto biscuits.
Pour egg mixture on top then sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: cheese-egg bake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom with one layer of bread slices, crusts trimmed off.
Spread cheese and ham over bread.

title: real scottish shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Put in a 5 x 9-inch pan. Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.
Put in tin to remain fresh.

title: almost nothing dish
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain peas. Then mix all ingredients together while macaroni is still hot.

title: cannoli shells
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together, then the liquid ones and mix well together.
Roll out dough and put around a wooden handle (use handle from broom which is well sanded), about 5-inches long.
Cut handle to 5-inch long pieces.
Yields about 25 small 5-inch long pieces.

title: barbecued ham sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham and buns; cook slowly, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Add ham; cook 10 minutes more. Split and toast buns.
Serve ham mixture over buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add buttermilk and blend well.
Add melted Crisco and blend well.
On lightly floured surface, knead/fold.
Cut (use 2 1/2-inch cutter or jelly glass). Place in greased pan; turn biscuits over so grease is on top also. Bake at 400° in lightly greased pan until brown.

title: ranch casserole
directions: Melt butter and brown meat, onion, garlic and salt.
Drain. Mix beans, soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix meat and bean mixture. Place in casserole dish that has the crushed tortillas in bottom. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: no cook divinity(easiest ever)
directions: Combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl; on low speed, or by hand, gradually blend in confectioners sugar.
Stir in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry at least 12 hours. Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Bring chicken broth and water to a slow simmer.
Add garlic, green onion, cilantro and salt.
Simmer gently.
Meanwhile, prepare and place into separate bowls, avocados, tortillas, beans and cheese.
After broth has simmered for 20 minutes, the meal is ready to serve.
Ladle broth into bowls and let your guests add the ingredients they prefer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into thick slices. Boil in water 10 minutes or until tender. Do not overcook.
Drain well and place in bowl with garlic, salt, pepper, oil, vinegar and oregano.
Let stand in marinade 12 hours before serving.

title: speedy spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat shortening in skillet over medium flame (300° if using burner-with-a-brain).
Add beef and garlic and fry, stirring until beef is well browned.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower flame (200° on burner-with-a-brain).
Cover skillet and simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti or macaroni.
Top generously with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired. Yield:
4 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Boil water and sugar 1 to 2 minutes.
Add strong tea and jello.
Add all fruit juices and let stand for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, add Hawaiian Punch and ginger ale.
Add ice before serving or use ice ring.

title: phil cream cheese icing
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Adding 1/2 pound more powdered sugar makes icing thicker.
Ices two cakes.

title: pineapple carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan boil the carrots, water and salt, covered, until carrots are tender, about 8 minutes.
Turn into a strainer to drain.
Add cornstarch to the empty saucepan off heat; gradually stir in pineapple juice.
Cook gently, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add carrots and pineapple and, if you like, a small amount (a generous tablespoon) of drained carrot liquid.
Heat. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Spread salted peanuts on a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put sugar in a heavy skillet and stir it over medium heat until it is completely melted and free of lumps.
Pour quickly over the peanuts and leave alone until it's hard.

title: baked doves with apple dressing
directions: Combine water and salt in a saucepan; add doves.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside. Spoon Apple Dressing into a lightly greased baking dish; arrange doves, breast side down, on top of dressing.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until birds are well browned.
Yields 6 to 12 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until knife comes out clean, about 25 minutes, at 325°.

title: green beans and tomato
directions: Heat oil in skillet and brown onion and green pepper.
Add tomato and cook for 5 minutes.
Add beans, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Turn into a serving dish and top with croutons. Serves 4.

title: baked carrots
directions: Parboil carrots, spread in buttered baking dish.
Cover carrots with soup (undiluted).
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Eat!!

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Soak tomatoes or cucumbers for 24 hours.
Wash and soak in clear water.
Boil all other ingredients and pour over tomatoes and let set for 24 hours.
Boil tomatoes in syrup for 25 minutes, put in jars, and peel.

title: dot's moist bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and water.
Add margarine and let melt.
Pour over bread to soften.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Set dish in shallow pan of hot water to bake.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, or until knife blade inserted near middle comes out clean.
A very nourishing dish.

title: banana crunch salad
directions: Wash, core and slice apples.
Quickly dip in lemon juice; drain.
Peel and slice bananas.
Dip in lemon juice; drain.
In medium size mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise and peanut butter. Mix well.
Stir in sunflower seeds.
Stir in apple slices until well coated.
Add bananas; do the same.
Put lettuce leaves on 6 plates; spoon mixture on.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: overnight sausage souffle
directions: Brown and degrease sausages.
Cut bread, cheese and sausage into bite-sized pieces.
(I grate the cheese.)
Layer in 2-quart casserole, bread, cheese and sausage.
Best if you repeat once. Pour butter over.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, mustard and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350° after it is at room temperature.
For double recipe, bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: quick rolls or bread
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast in large bowl.
Add enough flour to make batter.
Cover and let rise until light, about 30 minutes. Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and eggs.
When mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add to yeast mixture.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well.
Place in covered bowl. Let rise 30 minutes.
Shape into rolls or loaf.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake rolls at 400° for 20 minutes.
Bake loaves at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves or 30 rolls.

title: mom's apple strudel
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk until smooth.
Melt butter in a deep pan.
Fill pan 3/4 full of apples.
Pour flour mixture over apples.
Bake until brown.
Use tender apples.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries in greased pan.
Add pineapple.
Sprinkle on nuts and pour 1/2 cake mix over fruit.
Dot with margarine.
Add remaining cake mix and smooth down.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cream cheese frosting will certainly add to the flavor of the cake.

title: iced gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Mix together dry ingredients.
In a bowl, mix together milk, butter, honey, egg and ginger.
Make a well in center of flour. Add milk all at once; toss with a fork until dry ingredients are just mixed (do not overmix).
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake until brown and tests done, about 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Loosen loaf by running a metal spatula around side of pan.
Turn loaf out onto rack to cool completely.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins, drain and flour with 1 cup of flour.
Mix applesauce and soda until smooth.
Add sugar and eggs; beat.

title: favorite fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juice.
Add pudding mix to 2 cups of juice.
Sprinkle with Tang and beat until thickened.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: anytime fruit cobbler
directions: *Canned fruit in light or heavy syrup works best, but fresh fruit works well, also.

title: chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until onions are transparent.
Stir occasionally.
Serves six.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add whole tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook cabbage and onion until tender.
Brown ground round or chuck.
Drain.
Add all ingredients and cook.

title: hot sweet mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Pour into a double boiler.
Cook, stirring constantly (about 7 to 10 minutes) until smooth and thickened.
Store in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken.
Cut
in
small pieces and place in buttered baking
dish.
Mix
soup
and
sour cream and pour over chicken. Crush
crackers and combine with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except kisses in a large bowl.
Mix on lowest speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls (using a teaspoon).
Roll balls into sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Put a Hershey's kiss in center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients about 10 minutes. Stick cloves in orange and lemon rinds and float on top of punch.

title: turkey or chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; arrange in buttered cooking dish.
Then layer chicken or turkey.
Combine soup, cheese, mayo, juice, and curry powder.
Pour over broccoli and chicken (turkey).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs mixed with melted butter and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook shells, being careful not to overcook.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, honey, celery, onion, green pepper, celery seed, Old Bay seasoning and salt and pepper.
Combine crab legs and shells in large bowl.
Mix in dressing.
Chill well before serving.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain fruit well; let stand 12 hours in refrigerator.
Mix all together.
Add sour cream and marshmallows.

title: fattening salad
directions: Drain all fruit. Add softened cream cheese to mixed fruit and stir lightly. Add Cool Whip and marshmallows. Mix together. Refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours. Best when made a day before.

title: banana split supreme
directions: Crust:
Mix the first stick of margarine and the graham crackers and pack in a 9 x 13-inch dish; chill.

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix together in a large bowl.
Marinate overnight in:

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly; stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then bake another 30 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Add oil and Sucaryl.
Cream until light. Beat eggs until foamy.
Combine with first mixture.
Add rest of ingredients slowly.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into long loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss and mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit as a side dish.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and eggs (not together).
Debone chicken and place on bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add can of peas or mixed vegetables evenly.
Add chopped onion and eggs.
Spread over top, cream of chicken and cream of celery soup.
Mix together flour, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
If top is not brown enough, broil on top to finish browning to suit.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all fruit juices.
Put in ice.
Pour ginger ale over all and add strawberries.

title: korean spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in Dutch oven; cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Drain off fat.

title: pick-up-sticks-chicken
directions: May add any other spices to taste.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt first 3 items and pour over rice and onion in casserole. Cook 1 hour at 400°.
Cover if it gets too dry.

title: myra's soup
directions: Cook hamburger with cut-up green peppers; drain.
Combine all ingredients; put in a large pot.
Cook 2 hours.
Add water as needed; cook until desired consistency is reached.

title: crunchy clusters
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper. Over low heat, melt chips with Eagle Brand; remove from heat. In large bowl, combine noodles and peanuts. Stir in chocolate mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let set until firm. Store at room temperature.

title: dutch oven doves
directions: Salt and pepper birds to taste.
Make a paste of flour and butter and rub each bird with paste.
Place birds in baking dish and place a strip of bacon across each bird.
Bake in slow oven (300° to 325°) for about 1 hour.

title: cheese buttons(german dish)
directions: Mix well. Roll out thin. Cut in 3-inch squares.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine water and cranberries.
Bring just to a boil; reduce heat.
Boil gently, uncovered, over medium heat for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(Skins will pop.) Remove from heat.
Mash slightly.
Stir in Equal Measure.
Cover and chill.
Serve chilled with beef, pork, ham or poultry.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or 12 two tablespoon servings.

title: halloween pumpkins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine milk, coconut, 3 tablespoons gelatin, almond flavoring and food coloring (to tint).
Form into small balls (about 1/2 tablespoon).
Sprinkle remaining gelatin into dish; roll each ball to coat.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill. Cloves can be stuck on balls.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in cup of boiling water, then add 1 cup cold water.
Put cream cheese in mixture and whip.
Dissolve marshmallows in pineapple juice.
Fold in whipped cream and chill.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Half each piece of fruit except pineapple slices.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Roll each piece of fruit in mixture, coating lightly.
Arrange fruit in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole and pour sherry over top.
Mix oats, flour and salt together; sprinkle over fruit.
Pour melted butter over all, moistening the oat mixture well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Pour peaches with juice in bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle on cake mix dry.
Sprinkle coconut and walnuts on top.
Pour melted oleo over top and bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Check at 45.

title: egg batter bread
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add butter.
Gradually add water. Beat 2 minutes at medium with electric mixer.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup flour and beat at high speed two minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double, about 35 minutes.
Punch down.
Turn into 2 well-greased loaf pans or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover. Let rise again, about 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Prepare at least one ear of corn per person.
Don't take shuck off the corn.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a loaf pan; bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
May be made into muffins and cooked for about 30 minutes.
When cool, may be wrapped and stored in freezer for future use.

title: excellent pie crust
directions: Measure ingredients before mixing together.
Don't guess!!! Makes 3 single crusts.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon in large
pot
until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Brown onions in
bacon
fat.
Add
red
pepper and potatoes.
Cover with water
and cook until potatoes are soft. Add clams and simmer a few minutes.
Add soup, milk and bacon. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: berry punch
directions: Puree strawberries in a blender.
Combine all ingredients in a 6-quart bowl and serve.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter and white sugar, add coconut and vanilla, mix well.
Mix in flour.
Chill for 1/2 hour then make into rolls. Wrap rolls in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Cut thin slices 1/8-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork and bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.
Watch so they don't burn. Roll in powdered sugar.
Yields about 4 dozen.
They freeze well.

title: grilled mexi-potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Pour into aluminum pan.
Add 1 jar of salsa. Add 1 jar mushrooms.
Salt to taste.
Add margarine.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Place on hot grill.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and divide mixture in half.
Put chocolate chips in one half and chocolate syrup in the other half. Pour chocolate syrup half in pan first.
Top with chocolate chip mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done (pound cake pan).

title: communion bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixer until not sugary.
Add cream and as much flour as can be beaten in with mixer.
Add more flour and knead until dough is golden and bubbles form.
Roll on cookie sheet without flour.
Mark in inch strips, prick with fork 1/2 inch apart on sheet.
Makes enough for 50 people (about 3 1/2 c. Flour).

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Cover with beaten egg whites and sprinkle with grated orange rind (if desired).
Put back in oven until meringue is brown.

title: cheese ball(this is a quick cheese ball to fix for any party.)
directions: Cut eggs oblong, scoop out yolk and place in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika, and mix well.
Spoon mixture into egg center and sprinkle paprika on top.

title: baked chicken in sour cream
directions: Cut breasts in half and remove skin.
In bag, place flour, salt, pepper and shake chicken in bag to cover well.
In skillet, mix 1/4 cup oleo and 1/4 cup Wesson oil; brown chicken slightly on both sides.
Chop 2 medium onions fine.
Move chicken and sauce from skillet into casserole (may need 2).
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Scoop over and around approximately 1 pint sour cream. Cover tightly and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When partially set, whip with a mixer and then add remaining ingredients.
Chill in the refrigerator until set.
Unmold and garnish with lettuce and sliced cucumbers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except lemon slices and shrimp.
Pour about 1/2 cup sauce to cover bottom of a large baking dish.
Arrange a layer of shrimp and lemon slices. Alternate, leaving room at top.
Pour balance of sauce over contents.
Bake, uncovered, stirring once or twice until shrimp are bright pink, about 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve with French bread chunks and dunk into sauce.

title: texas chili beef slices(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer according to package directions. In small bowl, make marinade by combining onion, garlic, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Place steak in shallow baking dish.
Pour marinade over meat; store in refrigerator overnight or at least 3 hours.
Remove steak from marinade.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients except butter beans.
Heat a few minutes.
Put butter beans in 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over beans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cake mix sticky buns
directions: Combine cake mix, yeast, flour and water in a large bowl; mix to form dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Combine oleo, brown sugar, pecans and syrup in a bowl.
Spread in two (9 x 10-inch) baking pans.
Heat in oven (350°) until mixture is caramelized. Cool.

title: bavarian style chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oil in skillet until meat just turns white (approximately 5 minutes).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and chicken broth.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, separating vegetables with a fork and stirring frequently. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
In a small bowl combine sour cream, flour and paprika.
Stir into vegetables and heat gently.
Serve with green salad and cherry tomatoes.

title: sangria roja(sangria with red burgundy)
directions: Combine all the ingredients and stir to blend.
Add ice cubes and serve.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: french fish soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until cooked.
Add wine, sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Add all seafood and cook until clams and mussels open.
Serve with toasted garlic bread.

title: italian salami and cheese croissants
directions: Preheat broiler.
Brush bread slices with olive oil; season with garlic and pepper.
Broil 1 side of bread slice until toasted. Top with salami and cheese, folding cheese under to fit.
Sprinkle with oregano, then broil until cheese melts.
Top with parsley. Serve immediately.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients listed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: quick party log cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot (not boiling) water.
Transfer to small bowl; cool 5 minutes.
Blend in sour cream, vanilla and salt. Add confectioners sugar; beat until smooth.
Place pound cakes end to end to form one long cake.
Form log by rounding edges and corners.
Cut cake longways to make 3 layers.
Fill and frost.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lavender salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Stir in blueberry pie filling and cultured sour cream.
Stir a couple times while getting stiff. Refrigerate.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Cover apples with dip and roll in chopped nuts.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine egg, tuna, tuna liquid, mustard and half the bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Shape into four patties.
Roll in rest of crumbs.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar; cool.
Stir in egg, flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat tortillas in foil for 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
For sauce, in medium saucepan, cook onion, garlic, coriander and pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir flour into sour cream; add to onion mixture.
Stir in broth and chili peppers. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup of the cheese.

title: oyster mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Cream cheese with mayonnaise until smooth.
Add oysters and other ingredients; blend well. Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs gently with sugar; add oil, water and pumpkin.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour in three loaf pans at 350°.
Freezes great.

title: applesauce cake(no eggs)
directions: Bake in greased and floured loaf pan in moderate oven until toothpick comes out clean.
(No eggs; usually moist.)

title: baked brie
directions: Cut Brie in half; slit it!
Place 1/2 round on rolled
out roll dough.
Cover with 1/2 jar preserves.
Cover with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Place other 1/2 round on top.
Repeat layers. Bring dough up over top of all.
Brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix together and cook slowly until thick.
Delicious on ham!

title: heavenly squares
directions: Melt till smooth and remove from heat.
Cool and then add 2 1/2 c miniature marshmallows and nuts.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and chop.
Slice onion and saute in butter. Add flour and mix it all up.
Add curry and stock; heat at medium to thicken a bit.
Add broccoli and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle cheese on soup before serving.

title: after church pork chops
directions: Spread pork chops with mustard.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Shake chops in bag to coat with flour; then brown in oil.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and water. Mix well. Add flour. Mix and add pecans. Chill for 4 hours. Shape in balls or fingers. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. Remove when cooled slightly and roll in powdered sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: salsa chicken melt
directions: Top 1 bread slice with cheese single, salsa, chicken and second bread slice.
Spread sandwich with margarine.
Cook in skillet on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: spritz(press cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix butter, sugar, egg, salt and flavoring thoroughly. Measure flour and work into mixture. Using 1/4 dough at a time, force through cookie press on ungreased
baking sheet in desired shapes. Bake 6 to 9 minutes or until set but not brown. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: apricot candy
directions: Combine apricots, nuts and coconut; chop very fine.
Mix with orange rind and lemon juice.
Shape into balls and then roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugar coated and no syrup remains.
Pour into ungreased cooking sheet, scattering peanuts out with a fork. Put in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Stir after ten minutes, then return to oven.
Makes about 1 pound of candy.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, cream of tartar, syrup and oleo together. Boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda.
After foaming stops, pour over popcorn and mix.
Pour onto 2 cookie sheets; press down. Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes 6 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour broccoli in baking dish and add hot water.
Chop up broccoli; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: california dessert
directions: Mix and place first 3 items in greased 9-inch baking dish.
Top with mixture of rest of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until dry ingredients are dissolved thoroughly.
Line a shallow baking pan with foil.
Place pieces of chicken on the foil.
Pour sauce over chicken, making sure each piece is coated with sauce.
Seal foil. Place in oven heated to 500°.
Cook for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Baste every 20 minutes for more barbecue flavor.
If desired, foil may be opened for last 20
minutes to make chicken slightly crispy.

title: armenian easter bread
directions: Beat 4 eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, butter or margarine and milk.
Mix all well.
Add flour and yeast, mixed with 1/2 cup of warm water and a pinch of sugar.
Oil hands and knead dough.
If dough is sticky, add more flour as needed to make dough soft.
Set aside to rise to double its size.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Melt margarine with garlic powder.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip breast halves into margarine and coat with crumb mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining margarine over breasts.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes at 350°.

title: whipped potatoes with horseradish
directions: Combine potatoes with all except tomatoes.
Beat until fluffy. Place tomatoes in baking dish.
Salt and pepper them.
Top with potato mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: deanira's steak
directions: Brown meat with onion. Drain.
Pour in tomato sauce and 1 can of water (you can use more or less water, depending on how you like your sauce).
Simmer for 2 hours or until your meat is tender.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Salt and pepper to taste. Drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix soups, beef and noodles together.
Put in a baking dish.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter and Crisco.
Add and mix brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add the flour and soda.
Mix well and shape into rolls.
Roll up in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all powdered ingredients.
Store in sealed jars and use as needed.
Use 3 teaspoons in hot water per cup to be served.

title: pistachio nut salad
directions: Let Cool Whip soften to mixable.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.
Will be a slight lime color.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; blend in flour.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter and press into tiny lightly greased muffin tins.

title: raisin honey drops
directions: Cream honey, sugar, butter and egg; sift together the dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Mix until blended.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake on upper shelf of moderate hot oven (375°). Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on racks. Yields 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ground meat goulash
directions: Brown the ground meat, onion and garlic.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the potato.
Add just enough water to suit thickness.
Cube the potato; simmer until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli; separate and drain.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into well-greased baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out almost clean. Top will be golden brown.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Strain corn, green beans, onions and mushrooms and mix together.
Cook ground beef, then strain excess grease.
Pour and mix ground beef with mixture in an ovenware dish.
Mix in 1 1/2 tablespoons sour cream thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice Velveeta and cover contents in dish.
Pour crushed crackers over all contents in dish.
Cook in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve 4.

title: butter pecan turtle cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Mix at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl often, 2 to 3 minutes or until particles are fine.
Pat firmly into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over unbaked crust.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat steak with seasoned flour.
With wooden mallet, pound meat between wax paper until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 6 serving pieces.
Heat oil; brown steak well, all sides.
Saute onion until tender.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots.
Cover; simmer 1/2 hour or until meat and carrots are tender.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle this mixture onto bottom of baked pie crust.
Save some crumbs for top of the pie.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Beat in egg and add flour to mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch diameter balls and place on lightly sprayed or greased cookie sheet.
Flatten rolls with fork and bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Make well in center; add eggs and oil.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Blend in food coloring. Spoon batter into two 8-inch greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy oven roast beef
directions: Place roast on heavy-duty aluminum foil or in a covered dish or small roasting pan.
Brush with steak sauce and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Spoon mushroom soup on top and then sprinkle the 3 tablespoons of ground paprika on top of soup.
Potatoes and carrots may be placed around roast before baking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Beat the eggs.
Mix in the oil and sugar.
Mix in the zucchini and skins, nuts and vanilla.
Sift and mix the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine batter mixture with dry ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with tomato slices.
Dot with butter and dressing.
Cover with corned beef and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven. Separate each biscuit into 3 parts.
Cover top with biscuits, overlapping them.
Sprinkle with crackers and caraway seed.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: beef-tomato dinner
directions: Brown beef.
Pour off fat.
Add onion, parsley flakes, tomato paste, water, salt, chili powder and mushrooms.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Add macaroni and bring again to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles until done.
Brown ground beef.
Mix cream of mushroom coup, olives, hunts sauce, mushrooms and beef all together.
Grease 9 x 12 pan, start with a layer of spaghetti noodles, then spoon on sauce mixture, sprinkle cheddar cheese on and continue with process until the top of the pan.
Sprinkle the top with parmesan cheese and bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine; remove from heat. Add sweetened condensed milk, flour, vanilla, salt and eggs; mix well. Reserving 1/4 cup coconut for garnish, stir in remaining coconut and nuts. Pour into shell; garnish with remaining coconut. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until top is firm and coconut is lightly browned. Cool thoroughly before cutting. Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In bowl, break bread into small pieces.
Add vegetables and chicken. Blend in mayonnaise.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan and spread evenly. Beat eggs. Add milk and pour evenly over chicken mixture. Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, spread undiluted soup over filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix together.
Fry in butter.
Top with slice of Velveeta cheese.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt unsweetened chocolate and Crisco.
Mix other ingredients.
Add melted chocolate mixture.
Mix by hand.
Add nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until it resembles cornmeal.
Add enough buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness on a floured board.
Cut and place on biscuit sheet. Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 large biscuits.

title: little league casserole
directions: Slice onions and cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Place on top of onion.
Salt and pepper.
Spread uncooked ground beef, then tomato bits; cut bacon slices in half and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; arrange cheese in triangle on top the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: cheese jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Heat pineapple and add cheese. Spread until melted. Mix with jello and put in refrigerator until almost set. Fold in Cool Whip and chill until set.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Oil, but do not flour, a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer coconut and chopped pecans on the bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix using directions on box.
Pour over coconut and chopped pecans.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
After the cake has cooled, turn over. Dust with powdered sugar on top, if desired.

title: noodles nestled
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2 lengthwise; cut halves lengthwise.
Peel the 4 quarters.
Remove larger seeds.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices. Saute onion and garlic.
Saute eggplant slices.
Add tomato sauce. Fry hamburg.
Add all together but be sure to drain off hamburg grease.
Serve over wide noodles, macaroni elbows or rice.
Add favorite seasonings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients and boil 10 minutes.
Can in hot sterilized jars.

title: marian's cheese spreads
directions: Combine all cheeses until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread on crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups spread.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: apple cake(low-fat)
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients into mixing bowl; blend.
Add eggs, vanilla, applesauce and juice.
Stir just until blended.
Fold in apples.
Spoon batter into 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Combine egg white, water, salt and spices; beating until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Dip pecan halves, one at a time, into the egg white mixture.
Place pecan halves 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Store in an airtight container. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken and carrots
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon oil, cook chicken until it loses its pink color and is tender, about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove to bowl with a slotted spoon.

title: flank steak stir-fry
directions: Cut steak diagonally into thin strips.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in wok over high flame; stir-fry steak 5 minutes or until brown.
Push up sides; add remaining oil.
Stir-fry pepper for 2 minutes.
Add onion.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender, then mix with steak.
Combine soy sauce, cornstarch and water; add to wok, cooking until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oly koeks (dutch doughnut balls)(colonial recipe)
directions: Take up the dough with a spoon.
Add 2 raisins in each.
Fry in deep fat.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and gelatin; add oil.
Beat in eggs, add water and strawberries.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Frost with following icing.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broccoli, water, half and half, white pepper, baking soda and chicken bouillon; bring to a boil. While waiting for soup to boil, in small skillet, slowly melt butter, adding flour.
Stir slowly with a wire whisk, making sure there are no lumps.
After soup comes to a boil, reduce heat and add butter-flour mixture, stirring slowly with a wire whisk.
When soup has reached desired thickness, return to light boil for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in flour.
Add water and cook until thick.
Blend in cheese; add broccoli.
Fold in eggs. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs (enough to top the casserole).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake in 350 degree oven until brown on top and middle is well done.

title: bob lloyd's yankee chili
directions: Pam the bottom of stew pot.
Add ground beef.
Salt generously with Lawry's.
Add chili powder.
Cook on low heat until browned. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and beans.
Fill each can with water and add to mixture.
Add spaghetti to other ingredients; bring to boil.
Turn on low heat and cook 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove separated fat.
Heat before serving.
Add 1 tablespoon honey to each bowl.
Serve.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Spread onto serving dish with sides.
Chill for 6 hours.
Top with cocktail sauce and crabmeat prior to serving.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream softened cheese and 1 cup margarine in mixer bowl.
Blend in flour.
Chill dough at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips over low heat.
Add sugar gradually, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk, a little at a time, stirring constantly and allowing the mixture to return to a boil between additions.
When all milk is used, add vanilla.
Cool partially before using.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Place 3/4 of the crumbs in long cake pan. Spoon creamed mixture over this. Spread with a damp spoon.
Place sliced strawberries on this.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over this.
Top with the whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: Mix sour cream and 1/3 of Cool Whip, retaining balance of Cool Whip for topping.
Mix pudding with milk.
When thickened, add sour cream and Cool Whip mixture.
Layer in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish in the following order:
First the vanilla wafers, then bananas and pudding, ending with pudding.
Spread Cool Whip balance on top. Chill and serve.
Enjoy.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla flavoring for 1 minute. Take off and put in peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix up.
Put on wax paper.

title: basic sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve two cakes of yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add to milk mixture; beat in two eggs and add grated rind of lemon and enough flour to make a soft mold.
Put dough in greased bowl; let rise.
Take half of dough, put on floured board and roll into a ring.
Let it set a few minutes to relax.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick; cut with round cookie cutter.
Make a long dent through each round; dab with butter and fold top over and place on cookie sheet to rise.
Repeat the same with the other half of dough.
When they have raised to about double in size, bake in 375° oven until brown.
Can be stored in a plastic bag after they have cooled and used the next day by warming them in the oven.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add 3 cups flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Mix remaining 1 cup flour with fruit and coat well.
Add to batter; mix well.
Pour in tube pan that has been lined and greased with brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Allow cake to cool in pan.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 1-quart bowl or measuring cup. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes until blueberries are soft. Can be used over cake or ice cream or on hot cereal. Makes 1 pint.

title: quick supper dish
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Chop whole tomatoes and add with juice. Put cabbage on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium pan.
Whisk in milk until smooth.
Add egg yolks and whisk until blended.
Stir in peel and juice.
Add butter.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, 4 to 5 minutes or until thick.
Do not boil!!
Refrigerate until cool.
Fold in sour cream and put in 9-inch baked and cooled pie shell.

title: steckrueben oder kohlrabi(sauce over kohlrabi)
directions: Peel kohlrabi; slice or dice and boil in small amount of salted water until just tender.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid. Add butter and sugar to kohlrabi.
In small jar, mix flour and reserved, cooled liquid; shake well.
Pour over cooked kohlrabi, heat and stir gently until thickened; add milk.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten out chicken by pounding with mallet.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese and 1 slice ham.
Roll up chicken breast and stick 1 to 2 toothpicks through it to hold it together.
Add chicken broth. Put in 350° oven until cheese starts melting.
Prepare rice.
Place rice on plate and put 1 or 2 Cordon Bleu on top.
Serve and enjoy.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preset oven to 350°.
Mix the ingredients well (best to use clean hands).
Shape into small
balls about the size of a walnut. Place on cookie sheet and	bake
at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until light brown.	Can
be frozen.
Great at cocktail parties or brunch.

title: peppermint candies
directions: Chill good.
Pat out into patties.
Put patties into freezer. Keep freezer until ready to dip.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Trim crust from bread, butter and cut into cubes.
Beat eggs; add milk and bread cubes.
Stir broccoli and cheese into egg mixture.
Pour into buttered oblong baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: parmesan corn chowder
directions: To the water add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer; do not drain.
Make a white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add corn and undrained vegetables. Heat, but do not boil.
Add crumbled cooked bacon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Open and drain juice from both cans of pineapple into dish. Melt 24 large marshmallows into juice.
Cool.
Then mix pineapple into syrup, add Cool Whip and mix well.
Put in the graham cracker crusts. Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps well several days.

title: oma's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add nuts and flour.
Make little balls and bake at 350° until done.
Roll them in the powdered sugar after they have cooled.

title: grandmama's shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 cups flour at a time; mix well. Make into balls the size of a tennis ball.
Press out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in 6ths like you cut a pie.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes (do not brown).
Use waxed paper to press out balls.

title: shrimp and pasta stir-fry
directions: Combine mayonnaise, chicken broth and grated lemon rind with wire whisk.
Coat wok with spray.
Add ginger root and garlic; fry 1 minute.
Add shrimp and veggie; fry 3 minutes.
Add mayo mixture and pasta; cook until heated.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.

title: chicken livers for iron-needing mommies-to-be that hate chicken
directions: Saute all ingredients slowly in the margarine until done. Season to taste.
Add a little yogurt to cut the liver taste further.
Mash with a fork or grind in a food processor.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes for dinner or freeze in very small servings to be defrosted later and eaten on crackers as an appetizer.
It is quite yummy and liver makes me gag!!

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer in order listed.
Great with large tortilla chips of your choice.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients for 2 minutes on medium speed. Add jimmies and chips by hand.
Pour into a 12-cup greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack 15 to 20 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix together until smooth.
If desired add nuts or coconut. Put into prebaked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: caramel devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once (cake flour), measure, add soda, sift together. Cream butter or margarine thoroughly, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate and blend.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat until smooth Add vanilla.
Bake in 2 deep greased pans (9-inch) in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Spread with caramel or chocolate frosting.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries; heat juice and Coca-Cola.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add cherries and pineapple and chill.
When Jell-O is set, add sour cream and coconut.

title: buttermilk cornmeal pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.

title: jiffy goober haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter slowly in microwave. Stir until well blended. Add peanuts and noodles. Stir until well coated. Form into clusters on wax paper. Allow to harden. Yields 3 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar; beat eggs and mix with lemon and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool a little.
Add mustard, when almost cool, pour and mix three salad mixture that has been mixed well.
Then top with grated cheese and on top of cheese, put can of coconut.
Do not use juice from fruit cocktail.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour with cheese.
Add to top of pineapple.
Add
butter and crushed Ritz crackers to top.
Bake at
350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Good as a side dish with ham or
chicken or may be served as a dessert topped with Cool Whip.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Make crumbs out of other ingredients; mix until well blended.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs; set aside.
Combine the rest of crumbs with liquid mixture; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup of reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove and chop stems.
Place caps in buttered shallow baking dish.
Melt butter; saute stems in garlic and butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Stuff cups. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead and refrigerated.

title: irene's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 3-quart baking dish. Pour 1/3 cup of ketchup on top and spread evenly.
Put 3 strips of bacon on top of ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: deluxe peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a Dutch oven; cook over low heat to soft-crack stage (270°).
Stir in peanuts; cook to hard-crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour into 2 warm buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pans and spread to edges of pan.
Cool and break into pieces. Yield:
3 pounds.

title: barbecue biscuit cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground meat, green pepper and onion in skillet sprayed with cooking spray.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar substitute, mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place each biscuit in an ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with cheese and continue to bake until cheese melts.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white and vanilla together; add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add nuts, stirring only until well-coated. Drop from teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake in 250 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and do not remove pecan kisses for an additional 30 minutes. Yield: 24 pieces.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine.
Cook to boiling; boil one minute.
Cool one minute.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoon.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk in double boiler. Add 2 cups chopped pecans. Drop on buttered cookie sheet. Put in freezer for 1 hour. Melt chocolate; dip candy in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix ingredients according to directions on box.
Pour into 3 layer pans and cook at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Leave layers in pan about 5 minutes.
Remove and cool thoroughly on racks.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Leave meat in big chunks.
Add onion. Cook over medium heat until tender.
Add water, soup, salt, corn and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and tomato (diced).
Add pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan muffins
directions: Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pecan dainties
directions: For tart shells, beat butter and cream cheese in 2 qt. batter bowl until smooth.
Add flour, mix until a soft dough forms. Cover; chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls of dough into cups of ungreased mini-muffin pan.
Press dough to form tart shell.

title: smackeroons
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Continue beating until stiff but not dry.
Add sweetener and flavoring. Beat until well blended.
Fold in cereal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix, shake well and pour over greens.

title: pickled onions
directions: Place onions in large saucepan; cover with water.
Bring to boiling and simmer 2 minutes; drain.
Plunge into cold water and peel.
Put onions in large bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand for 12 to 18 hours; drain and rinse well.

title: choco-nut sandwich cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg, blending well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition. Stir in vanilla.

Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes. Cool cookies on wire racks. Spread about 2 tablespoons Coconut Cream Filling on bottom side of half the cookies.
Place remaining cookies, bottom side down, on top of filling.

title: curried turkey and ham croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange equal amounts of asparagus, ham, turkey and cheese on bottom half of each croissant.
Place top halves of croissants on cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Blend all ingredients. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients with spinach and chill for 2 hours.
Roll into balls.* Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine and work with hands until smooth and spongy.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.
Keep your hands wet while handling. Brown in skillet.
Place soup in container, add meatballs and up to 1 can milk.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: mamaw's "old timey" tea cakes
directions: Mix
sugar,
Crisco and eggs.
Add soda, salt and milk, then add
flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour exactly.
Remove from oven for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 375°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onions; drain. Mix together cream, enchilada sauce and soup. Pour some of the sauce mix into the bottom of a pan; add meat mixture. Cover with cheese slices and tortilla chips. Repeat layers, ending with sauce on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn.
Put the well popped kernels in a large bowl, discarding unpopped kernels.
Salt.
Combine corn syrup, molasses and vinegar in a saucepan.
Boil to 270°; remove from stove.
Add butter.
Pour slowly over popped corn; mix with a spoon.
Press lightly into balls as soon as it is cool enough to handle.

title: mom's filled coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, beating until smooth.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk to which vanilla has been added.
Pour into buttered deep 9-inch round pan.
Cover with crumb topping.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and when cold, split and fill with custard filling.
Serves 12.

title: salmon pate
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl, except pecans.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Add pecans and mix.
Use as dip or spread.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan (glass).
In separate bowl, mix mushroom soup and water together (as directions on can).
Pour half soup mix on top of rice; mix together.
Place 4 pork loins on top of rice.
Pour rest of soup on top; sprinkle with basil.
Cook for 1 hour, putting foil on top of dish for last 10 minutes of cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Rinse beans; pour off water.
Add about 4 inches of water.
Add barbecue sauce, molasses, liquid smoke, ketchup, link sausage (I use Eckrich or Hillshire Farms, 1/2 to 1 inch slices), garlic powder, onion powder or chopped onion (I use both) and bacon grease.
Cook for about 3 to 4 hours or until done.
Serve with corn bread.

title: potato chowder
directions: Combine half the potatoes with chicken broth in a saucepan with tight-fitting lid.
Bring to a boil; simmer until tender. Mash potatoes; stir in remaining potatoes, carrots, corn, celery, onion and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer until vegetables are tender. Dissolve flour in a little of the milk.
Stir into chowder with remaining milk and parsley.
Cook (stirring) over medium heat to thicken slightly.
Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: rice salad
directions: Toss gently and chill.

title: chocolate chip fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter 9 minutes.
