Stir occasionally. Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients, stirring until chips are melted.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour with soda and salt, beat into sugar mixture.
Fold in pecans and apples. Pour into tube pan, which has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Put all the ingredients (except buns) into crock-pot on low heat for 3 1/2 hours. Pull out and put in bowl. Shred beef with fork or potato masher. Put back in crock-pot on medium heat for an additional hour. Put on buns and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Note:
Use as much lettuce, onions, cheese and tomatoes as you want.

title: no cook chocolate cream cheese fudge
directions: Soften cream cheese in warm place.
Mix cocoa with sugar to get all lumps out of cocoa.
Cream in cream cheese; add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in dish and cool in refrigerator.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed figs(teen mihshee)
directions: Remove stems.
Combine orange juice, lemon juice, peel and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Add figs and heat to boiling point.
Simmer until fruit is tender.
Drain well.
Cool.
Insert knife in stem end of fig and stuff each fig with an almond.
Close opening and roll figs in 1/2 cup sugar.
Dry overnight before storing.

title: punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour lemon juice over bananas.
Combine sugar mixture, bananas and juices. Mix and freeze.
When you want to serve, let thaw an hour or so; add 7-Up, Sprite or ginger ale.

title: roasted bell peppers
directions: Heat olive oil; add minced garlic cloves and saute for a few minutes.
(Do not brown!)
Add peppers and bake at 250° for about 45 minutes, turning and basting often.
Cool and store in jar in refrigerator.
Use in salads, stews, soups, sandwiches, pizza, etc.

title: grandma drake's ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Scald milk (heat just to boiling point), remove from heat.
Slowly add scalded milk to sugar mixture stirring constantly.
Beat eggs.
Add about 1 cup of hot milk mixture to beaten eggs.
Add egg mixture to remaining milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until smooth and begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cool in refrigerator.
When cool, pour into 1 gallon freezer.
Pack with 4 parts ice and 1 part coarse salt around container.
Turn freezer, add salt and ice as needed. Takes about 30 minutes; 15 minutes in electric freezer.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat bacon grease (cook onion in it) for 11 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes; add to stock.
Add peppers, onion, thyme, bay leaf and salt to taste and cook for 11 minutes more. Add chicken and cook 1 1/2 hours.
When finished, put in 1 tablespoon gumbo file.
Do not boil after adding gumbo file.
Serve on rice.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk, and margarine.
Cook and stir.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, oats, and salt.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Can be doubled.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pack jar with cucumbers.
Heat vinegar, alum, pickling salt and mixed spices.
Heat and pour over pickles.
Finish filling jar with hot water; seal.
Two weeks before using, pour off liquid. To it, add sugar and heat.
Pour over pickles.
Cool and eat.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in hot oil (375° to 400°) until golden brown on one side.
Turn and cook until brown on other side.
Makes about 20 to 30 hush puppies.

title: rolled chicken thighs
directions: Place chicken in kettle and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil, then simmer until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and bone.
Cut into large pieces and add 3 tablespoons butter, if needed.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in 2-quart dish.
Arrange avocado over bean dip.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and garlic salt.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco mix.
Spread over avocado.
Top with layer of tomatoes and black olives.
Spread with cheese dip and sprinkle with green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: incredible chocolate cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix the brown sugar and cocoa.
Stir in water.
Add marshmallows.
Mix chocolate cake mix according to directions on package and spoon over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool; serve with Cool Whip.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill well until it starts to set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; cool.
Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon Jell-O. Stir in undrained pineapple.
Fold in whipped whipping cream. Spread over cherry layer.
Spread marshmallows on top.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar and beat in eggs.
Sift flour, nutmeg and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add more flour if needed to make a medium stiff dough.
Chill before rolling and fry in deep fat.
Place on paper towels after fried.

title: creole chicken gumbo(southern style)
directions: Cover chicken with water; season with salt and pepper and cook, covered, until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Measure out 3 cups of broth.

title: butter cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift and blend flour, salt and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: almond cheese pie
directions: Beat these three ingredients with a spoon.
Pour over pie (that has cooled for 20 minutes) and bake for 10 minutes more. Cool on a rack for 1 hour, then refrigerate.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add flour alternately with eggs.
Add lemon extract.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour in lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open door during baking.
Let cool in pan for 3 minutes.

title: marshmallow yam bake
directions: Line square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with pineapple.
Place drained yams on the top, along with 1/4 cup of the pineapple juice.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and salt until coarse crumbs and sprinkle over top of yams.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over yams. Broil until brown.
Serve.

title: california-style blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: cheese dip
directions: Have
cheese
at room temperature.
Combine ingredients and beat until smooth.	Chill until ready to serve.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut meat no thicker than 1/4 inch and as long as you can.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Add meat. Let meat set in mix for 24 to 30 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Place on paper towel and blot meat dry. Cook for 8 to 10 hours at 150°. Cook meat on oven rack and not in a pan.

title: divinity
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cover; place over moderate heat.
Heat to boiling.
Remove cover after 5 minutes.
Cook to very hard ball stage (260°).
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly. Add gradually to stiffly beaten egg white, beating constantly until very stiff.
Let cool, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop from buttered teaspoon onto cookie sheet.

title: no fuss lasagna
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Fry hamburger and drain.
Put hamburger on bottom of pan just to cover, then put some spaghetti sauce to cover.
Take your lasagna noodles, not cooked, and place over your hamburger and sauce.
Second layer, spread your cottage cheese and Ricotta cheese on the noodles, then spread sauce, then hamburger. Layer with lasagna noodles and spread a little sauce on top.
Pour 1/2 can of beer over lasagna and cover.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.
Uncover to brown top.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order listed in a large salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix; mix well. Spread over vegetables, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle sugar, then bacon and cheese.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: cheese lover's white pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Unroll pizza dough; press into prepared pan.
Arrange remaining ingredients over top.
Bake until cheese is bubbly and golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Each serving provides: 2P, 1/2 V, 1 1/2 B, 25C.

title: honey mustard
directions: Blend thoroughly. Good as a sauce to dip chicken strips or nuggets in.
Can also be used to marinate chicken or pork for baking or grilling.

title: beef and taters
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Add soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Put in baking dish and cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with grated cheese. Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini tomato salad
directions: Combine zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper and onion; toss lightly.
Combine vinegar, salt, garlic salt, pepper and salad oil; mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain and cool.
Add cheese, tomatoes and kidney beans. Blend together the mayonnaise and taco sauce. Add to hamburger mixture. Add lettuce and taco chips.
Mix together well just before ready to serve.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Bake at 325°.

title: banana bread(sugar-free)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Combine shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture stirring only until flour is moistened.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan and bake for 60 minutes or until done.
When done, mix 12 packets Equal with 2 tablespoons hot water and pour over bread.

title: oatmeal cornflake cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder and add gradually to first mixture.
With large spoon, add and mix the vanilla, oatmeal and cornflakes.
Form balls about the size of a small hickory nut on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: florence's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter good.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each egg.
Add powdered sugar half at a time.
Add flour in 3 additions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs; add extract.
Add dry ingredients and milk, alternating as you mix.
Mix well; stir in coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. (Do not overbake; cake should be moist.)

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in hot water.
Let cool, then add rest of ingredients.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked fresh ham, southern style
directions: Put meat in kettle and cover with boiling water.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Cool in the broth and refrigerate overnight.
Remove rind from ham. Mix mustard and horseradish and rub on fat.
Insert garlic in the fat.
Put on rack and bake in preheated slow oven (300°) for 2 hours.
Score fat with a knife, stud with cloves and sprinkle with the sugar.
Bake for 1 hour longer, basting occasionally with drippings in the pan.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Halve squash lengthwise; scoop out.
Trim bottom, if necessary, so squash will stand level.
Blend together honey, butter, salt and pepper and divide equally among the halves.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Boil 1 minute; remove.
Stir in 3 cups oatmeal.
Drop onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Do not refrigerate! Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili peppers and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer mixture for 10 to 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1/2 of the meat.
Cover with 2 tortillas and 1/2 of the pound of grated cheese.
Continue with meat mixture, tortillas and cheese.
Spread sour cream on the top of the casserole; sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until bubbly. Serves 8.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut dates and orange slices into small pieces.
Mix with chopped nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and pour over this and mix as fruit cake, adding remaining ingredients and mixing well. Bake in large oiled and floured tube pan at 300° about 2 hours. Cool in pan.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice thin and cook carrots.
Blend sugar and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in icebox at least 24 hours before serving.

title: pat's never fail rolled dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together, roll out on floured dough board and cut.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients except bread crumbs in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: In large bowl mix eggs on high until very frothy at 3 minutes. Add sugar, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon, milk and butter.
Beat on high speed until well blended.
Add raisins and nuts to mixture. Place bread in greased loaf pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread. Let sit 45 minutes, patting down occasionally.
Place in 350° oven immediately.
Lower temperature to 300°.
Bake 40 minutes. Increase oven temperature to 425°, 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serve warm with favorite sauce or ice cream.

title: red hot salad
directions: Place candy
and
water
in
pan over low heat and stir until dissolved
and near boiling; add to jello.
Then pour in applesauce
and
pineapple
(do
not drain pineapple); let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
Cream oleo, sugar and egg.
Add milk.
Add flour mixture to oleo and egg mixture.
Chill 15 minutes.
Place dough on lightly floured board. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Stir together and chill.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Let loaf rise according to directions.
Prepare filling; cook pork or beef with mushrooms, onion, salt and pepper in a large skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, paprika, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil, lower heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally; cool.
Punch down dough. Roll out on floured surface to a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
(You really have to push on the rolling pin.)
Lift dough to a greased cookie sheet.
Spoon meat filling down center third of dough. Sprinkle filling with cheese.
Make diagonal cuts in dough 1 1/2 inches apart down each side, cutting to within 1/2 inch of filling. Crisscross strips over filling, pressing down and seal with a drop of water.
(You may have to knead together or use toothpick to hold strips together.)
Brush top of dough with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in thick slices to serve.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Slice yams half inch thick. Slice apples thin. Place alternate layers starting with apples in glass or Corningware-type casserole. Boil water and butter. Mix sugar and cornstarch and enough water to form paste and add to water and butter. Mix and cook until clear and thickened. Pour over yam and apple. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured tube pan, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans with beef
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Put other ingredients in casserole.
Pour meat mixture over.
Cook about 45 minutes in a 350° to 400° oven.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Combine green peas, soup, pimento and eggs.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and oleo; spread over green peas mixture in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas together.
Smooth on top of a flour tortilla.
Then start from one edge and roll up. Repeat process until all ingredients are gone.
Refrigerate these logs for two (2) hours.
With sharp knife, cut logs into bite size pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: super salad
directions: Cook, drain and chill macaroni.
In separate bowl, mix all the other ingredients.
Stir sauce into noodles.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Keeps up to one week.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Mix in order and beat for 5 minutes.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple slump
directions: Combine apple slices, sugar, cinnamon and water in a saucepan with a tight-fitting lid.
Heat to boiling.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Stir in enough milk to make a soft dough. Drop dough from a tablespoon onto the apple mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with sauce or heavy cream.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa in bowl with fork.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla completely.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, softened margarine and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes.
Spread pineapple over creamed mixture.
Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours. Can refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with drained cherries.

title: pork chop-rice casserole
directions: In greased casserole, place pork chops, onion, pepper and rice.
Pour in water and undrained tomatoes.
Sprinkle with seasonings to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pennsylvania  apple pot pie
directions: Sift together the sugar and cinnamon.
Pare, core and cut apples into eighths.

title: beef spoon burgers
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until lightly browned.
Add meat, stirring until meat loses red color. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer uncovered over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Spoon hot onto split and toasted buns. Serves 12, but allow for repeats.

title: spicy salad dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add slowly, salad oil, then vinegar and celery seed.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute pepper and onion in cooking oil in heavy iron skillet. When soft, add ground meat and cook until done.
Add seasonings; stir thoroughly.
Add corn and tomatoes; heat mixture until hot, then add corn meal.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into Pyrex baking dish and bake in preheated oven (350°) until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread on cookie crust.
Place on pizza the strawberries, kiwi and oranges.

title: strawberry dessert pound cake
directions: Slice pound cake as thin as you can.
Place in long glass baking dish.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Mix 1/3 of Cool Whip mix with pudding.
Spread over cake.
Pour strawberry pie filling over pudding.
Slice bananas on top of strawberry filling. Sprinkle pecans over rest.
Then mix 1/2 box powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix together with rest of Cool Whip.
Spread on top.

title: baked ham appetizers
directions: Chop ham and onion.
Grate cheese.
Mix together (set aside). Mix margarine, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to make a spread for rolls.
Split rolls lengthwise and spread thin layer of spread on each side of rolls; fill with layer of ham, cheese and onion. Put tops back on.
Return to aluminum roll pans.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Make ahead and freeze, thaw before baking.)

title: celery stuffing
directions: Soften the cream cheese by microwaving 30 seconds.
Liquify onion, with olive juice, in the blender.
Mix thoroughly with the softened cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add a little more olive juice if it seems too stiff to blend easily.
Add stuffed olives and salt.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sauerkraut calico salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut
until	all
odor is gone.
Drain well! Combine sauerkraut, onion and green pepper. Set aside.

title: old-fashioned fruit cake
directions: Put flour in large mixing bowl; make large hole in center of flour.
Put in eggs, brown sugar, molasses, butter, vanilla, ginger and soda.
Mix gradually by hand, gently putting in a little flour at a time, until all flour is moistened and in large ball.
Divide into 6 even balls.
Roll each into 8-inch cake size. Put 1 roll between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Place dried apples between layers.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Line buttered baking dish with chipped beef.
Season chicken. Wrap 1 strip bacon around each chicken breast; place over chipped beef.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and a dash of Tabasco sauce; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 1 hour longer.

title: play doh(dough)
directions: Cook over medium heat until you can't stir anymore, then knead until smooth. Keep in airtight Baggie.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In a bowl mix together by hand the cottage cheese, fruit, nuts and Jell-O until well blended.
Add Cool Whip, blending well. If you would like a little more orange color, add 2 drops red and 2 drops yellow food coloring.
Refrigerate.
Looks nice served on a lettuce leaf.

title: orange cream fruit salad(very easy and very good)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen juice concentrate.
Add 1 small can mandarin oranges with juice.
Add undrained crushed pineapple.
Let set until firm.
Add topping.

title: chicken
directions: Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place breast and cheese; pour soup over breast and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing next. Last, add melted butter.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 50 minutes.

title: three bean bake
directions: Brown beef; drain and place in bean pot or crock-pot.
Brown onion and bacon; add to beef.
Do not drain.
Add brown sugar, dry mustard, white sugar, molasses, ketchup, chili powder, barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
To all ingredients, add red kidney beans, pork and beans and butter beans.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.

Microwave chocolate, butter and evaporated milk in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes at Medium-high (70% power) or, if using a compact microwave, High (100% power), until butter melts.
Stir until smooth and chocolate is melted. Stir in vanilla.
Beat in sugar gradually until mixture is smooth and creamy, but not crumbly. Stir in nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered pan.
Chill to firm (20 minutes).
Cut into squares.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: rich and creamy hot chocolate
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt. Whisk in water until blended. Stir over medium-high heat until boiling; boil 2 minutes. Add half and half, milk, cinnamon and chocolate, stirring just until chocolate is melted and liquid is heated through; do not boil. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla extract. Top with marshmallow, if desired. Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour together.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add vanilla flavor.
Pour it in a bowl full of bananas.
(Medium to low.)

title: baked ziti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 3-quart baking dish.
Set 2 cups of spaghetti sauce aside.
Stir remaining spaghetti sauce and herbs into pasta.
Place 1/2 of pasta mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Mix soup mixture together.
Salt and pepper.
Place rice in greased roaster.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until thick and smooth.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni; drain.
In heavy saucepan, make a basic white sauce by melting margarine.
Add onion, then flour.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then slowly add milk to desired thickness.
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Add Velveeta cheese; cook over low heat, stirring, until cheese is melted.
Pour over macaroni.
Stir in 1/2 shredded Cheddar cheese and pour into baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Grease 2 bread pans and sprinkle a topping of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon butter, mixed, over the dough in the pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: ham and cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oleo, cook ham and onion until ham is browned and onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot.
Garnish with parsley.

title: eggs
directions: Mix eggs, cheese and milk.
Put in microwave bowl and put in microwave on Cook for 3 minutes.
Stop and stir after each minute.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal with shortening and let stand for 1 hour.
Add well beaten eggs and mix sifted dry ingredients alternately with the water.
Add raisins last. Wash raisins before grinding for more moisture.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: savory cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and grease 12-cup muffin tin.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil and milk together.
Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Fold gently into egg mixture and stir in cheese and onion, mixing only until combined.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into muffin tin.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: fruit tea
directions: Place tea bags in boiling water and let steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags. Add sugar and stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed. Best if allowed to ripen in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust.
Combine graham crackers and margarine and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and take off of bones.
Cook beef, pork and onions.
Put everything in chicken stock.
Bring to boil, then turn down stove.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: onion-crusted chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Boil about 20 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Take off burner.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour in a buttered pan.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Eat and enjoy.

title: can't miss punch
directions: Add together.
Mix in a large punch bowl.
Add ice. Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. (I use a rectangular Pyrex dish.)
Microwave on High 15 to 18 minutes, covered with plastic wrap.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Core cabbage; blanch and drain.
While cabbage cools, slice French rolls into thin slices.
Arrange a layer of bread and a layer of cabbage leaves, topped with salt, pepper and cheese, in a lightly greased, deep baking dish.
Continue to layer, ending layers with one of cabbage.
Pour chicken broth into dish until just touches top cabbage layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Layer items (either individual salads or one large salad).

title: candied peanuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Boil until completely dry.
Put on baking sheet and crumble.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes. Keep tightly closed.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugars and eggs until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.

title: creamy chocolate glaze for chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Yields about 2 cups.
Spoon over Chocolate Pound Cake.

title: raisin krunchers
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan by rubbing lightly with shortening or butter.
Set aside.
Place peanut butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in large microwave-safe glass or plastic bowl.
Place bowl in microwave oven.
Turn microwave on High (100%) and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove bowl from microwave.
Add vanilla; stir with spoon until mixture is smooth.
Add rice cereal, oats and raisins. Gently stir without crushing cereal.
Spoon into prepared pan. Press mixture down firmly with fingertips to pack.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Wrap bars in plastic wrap.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: perfume(good scents)
directions: Will need medium-size bowl, soft cloth, saucepan, potholder, small funnel and tiny jar with lid.

title: carrot cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add warm water, then flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and apple slices.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with brown sugar. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: cranapple cider
directions: Heat to boiling.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spices and lemon. Serve hot.

title: summer soup
directions: Cut pork into slices (1/4-inch thick).
Cook pork in about 2 quarts of water about 45 minutes. Add all ingredients except corn and cook until beans are almost done.
Add fresh cut corn and if desired, small corn meal dumplings (size of a fifty cent piece). Cook about 20 minutes more.
Delicious!
Serve in shallow bowls.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to directions on box in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix milk and Kahlua with instant pudding.
Let set. Slice cake in small pieces.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: Bring milk and half and half to a boil.
Set aside until lukewarm. Mix yogurt and 2 cups of milk mixture well.
Put in a bowl with a tight lid and cover with a heavy blanket or quilt. Leave on counter for several hours, then refrigerate.

title: chicken rice dish
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix the mushroom soup, water and wine together and pour over rice. Roll cut pieces of chicken in dry onion soup and place on top of rice mixture.
Cover with lid or foil. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and check to see if liquid still in dish as some rice takes more liquid than others.
Finish baking, uncovered, 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Good leftover just adding water. Cover and warm up 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon doughnut drops
directions: In a large saucepan, heat 2 to 3 inches of oil to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, 1/3 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in milk, oil, vanilla and egg with a fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil, 5 to 6 at a time.
Fry 1 to 1 1/2 minutes
on each side until deep golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; roll warm doughnut balls in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Makes 24 to 30 balls.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350°
at least an hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt and mix well.
Blend in milk, then add rice, raisins, vanilla and spices.
Bake in greased, 1-quart baking dish.
Set inside shallow pan with 1 inch of water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; let cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While still warm, spread with topping.

title: orange and pineapple punch
directions: Mix juices and sherbets.
Add 2 trays each of pineapple juice and orange juice frozen with maraschino cherries.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar and meal.
Stir.
Add oleo, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake for about 30 minutes in 350° oven (or until pie doesn't shake much).

title: battered chicken stir-fry(for 4)
directions: Peel garlic; cut into 1/4-inch squares.
Crush with side of knife and chop finely.
Thin-slice green onions at white end and into 1-inch pieces at green end.
Slice raw chicken breasts into 1/4-inch strips and rub in salt and pepper.
Beat eggs lightly and dip chicken strips.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain green beans.
Cut tomato into wedges and slice onion into rings.
Combine all ingredients and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour dressing over all and chill.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and mix well.
Add bananas, buttermilk and soda.
Gradually mix in flour and salt. Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla cream frosting.
This cake stays very moist.

title: decorator's frosting
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and egg white in bowl; tint with food coloring.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix together pineapple, lemon juice, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Divide mixture in 2 pie crusts.
Put half cherry filling on each pie.
Top with crushed pecans.
Put in refrigerator. Delicious.

title: carolina chews
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spiced lamb with eggplant
directions: Sprinkle eggplant with salt; let stand 30 minutes.
Rinse and pat dry.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In a shallow dish, combine herbs and spices.
Roll lamb in mixture, pressing spices evenly into meat.
Heat 2 teaspoons oil.
Brown meat in batches for 5 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to roasting pan; add remaining 2 teaspoons oil to skillet.
Add eggplant, carrots, onion and whole garlic cloves. Cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add vegetables to roasting pan.
In same skillet, bring wine, stock, orange juice and tomato paste to boil, stirring.
Pour over lamb and vegetables. Cover and bake for 2 hours.
Boil sauce for 3 minutes to thicken. Serve over lamb and vegetables.
Garnish with fresh mint.
(Great with rice pilaf.)

title: chocolate pan cake
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar and salt.
In saucepan (I prefer microwave), bring water, margarine, cocoa and oil to a boil.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat in eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Pour into lightly oiled 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake bakes, make frosting and wash dishes!

title: bishop's wine
directions: Stud whole orange with cloves and heat in wine with cinnamon stick for 30 minutes.
Do not boil.
Stir in sugar.
Serve at once or keep hot in a double boiler.
Serves 8.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in small amount of boiling, salted water.
Drain.
Combine with onion and green pepper.
Combine soup, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and mustard.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly with a fork. Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn doggies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add eggs and milk.
Mix well. Dip hot dogs and fry.

title: caramel puffcorn curls
directions: Put puffcorn curls in a large roaster.
Boil margarine, syrup and brown sugar 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over puffcorn and bake, uncovered, at 250° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Add nuts, if you wish.
Pour on wax paper and break apart.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Wash squash and drop in boiling water.
Simmer for about 10 minutes or until tender-firm.
Drain and cool.
Cook vegetables of choice according to directions, drain and combine vegetable pulp, butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth (blender is helpful).
Pour into squash shells, sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and broil until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuit dough into 1/4ths.
Place in plastic bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Put in tube pan loosely.
Cook for 1 minute. Mix brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over bread.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 20 minutes.
Turn upside-down to remove.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup water, then add 1/2 cup cold water. Mix in pie filling and refrigerate.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
Spray a baking pan with non-stick spray.
Put seasoning or soup in a sealable container or empty bread paper.
Put potatoes in with seasoning, seal and shake until well coated.
Scatter potatoes on baking pan and bake until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: olive nut sandwich filling
directions: Mash cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, mix well.
Stir in pecans, olives, 2 tablespoons olive juice and pepper.
Do not add salt. Mix well.
Refrigerate for few hours before spreading on bread.

title: golden punch
directions: Chop wood, carry into house and build fire in stove.
Get out bowl, spoons and ingredients.
Grease pan and empty yeast in warm water.
Take toys off of table and give Peewee a spoon and let him help measure 2 1/2 cups flour.
Take Peewee's hands out of flour. Dust flour off his clothes.
Measure flour again to make up for what was knocked on floor.
Put flour, sugar, and salt in sifter. Take greased pan away from Peewee and put out of reach.
Pick up broken bowl and get another one.
Run chickens out of garden.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Divide a crate of peaches into three piles, using one pile at a time.
This prevents the peaches from becoming dark as peeled. Do not scald, but carefully peel, pit and slice.

title: chicken mexicana
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Melt butter over a medium heat.
Add chicken; cook for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over; add onion and pepper around the edge of the skillet.
Cook 5 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Place rice on serving platter; arrange chicken and the vegetables on the rice.
Keep warm.
Add picante sauce and the cheese to the skillet.
Cook and stir until the cheese is melted and sauce is hot.
Pour cheese sauce over chicken and vegetables.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with additional picante sauce.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Melt butter or margarine and combine with butter flavoring.
Pour over bread cubes.
Mix until bread is coated.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring frequently, 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour over buttered cubes.
Bake in 375° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Cut up small or diced vegetables and mix together.
Pour Italian dressing and Salad Supreme over top and mix well.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: In a glass jar, arrange alternate layers of cucumbers, carrots, bell peppers, onion and tomatoes.
Lightly sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper and scatter the black olives and rolled anchovies over the vegetables.

title: hot cider
directions: Mix together and warm.

title: zucchini bites
directions: Cook zucchini slices in steamer basket over boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cool slightly and drain well.
Working carefully, scoop some of the pulp out of each slice, forming a small cup to hold filling.
Be sure to leave small amount of pulp in bottom. Set aside.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill. Roll dough 1/8 inch thick. Cut in 1 1/2 inch rounds. Transfer to waxed paper heavily sprinkled with granulated sugar (I usually use granulated sugar instead of flour when I roll them out and they are already coated). Turn to coat both sides. Put on ungreased baking sheet. Prick with fork. Bake 7-9 minutes at 375°.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 tsp. salt and pepper in a large resealable plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake until well coated.
In a skillet, brown chicken in butter over medium heat.
Remove chicken; set aside and keep warm.
In the pan drippings, saute onion, green pepper and garlic until tender.
Add pimientos and rice.
Reduce heat; cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broth, turmeric, chili powder and remaining salt; bring to a boil.
Pour into an ungreased 2-qt. baking dish; top with chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken juices run clear and rice is tender.
Serves 2.

title: confetti macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Combine macaroni, luncheon meat, cheese, green pepper, onion and cucumber.
Stir well.
Chill.

title: tuna rice patties
directions: Rinse tuna in boiling water.
Steam rice.
Blend tuna with rice, combine with egg mixed with onion, parsley, flour and salt. Shape into flat cakes and brown in hot oil until golden brown. Serve with your favorite tomato sauce.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: skillet rice
directions: Season to taste with garlic powder, celery salt, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.

title: alamo elementary buttered rolls(yields 100)
directions: Mix yeast in pan with 4 cups warm water; stir.
Combine milk, sugar, salt, melted butter and yeast.
Add flour (use more if needed).
Let rise 2 hours.
Spray pan coating or thin layer vegetable oil and 2 cups melted butter (use enough butter to cover both sides).
Roll and cut.
Bake at 325°.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in next 4 combined dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until edges pull from side of pan.
Cut into squares when cool. Yields 16 servings.

title: brian bailey's chocolate cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream together and set aside the cream cheese, 1/8 teaspoon salt, egg, sugar and chocolate chips.
Mix flour, sugar, soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt and cocoa.
Mix well and add water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well and spoon into cupcake papers 1/3 full.
Drop 1 teaspoon of the cheese mixture (that was set aside) on top of the cake mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove if cheese mixture on top of cupcakes goldens before time is up.
Serve cool.

title: venison stew 2
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add other ingredients and cover.
Cook over low heat until meat is tender and vegetables cooked.
Add a little water if the gravy becomes too thick before the stew is cooked.
Stir occasionally to keep from burning.

title: easy pecan squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg; beat well.
Add vanilla, salt, nuts and flour.
Pour in baking pan and cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Cut into squares.

title: punch
directions: Soften sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet. Add vodka if desired.
Serve.
I use about 2 cups additional ginger ale.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Over medium heat in large skillet, saute garlic, onion and mushrooms for 3 minutes; remove with slotted spoon.
Add chicken to skillet and cook 5 minutes per side.
Add broth and soup; cook 5 minutes.
Return mushroom mixture to skillet and cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: chicken-ham roll-ups
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper; flatten with side of knife.
Top each breast with slice of ham.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
In skillet, brown roll-ups in butter.
Stir in soup and wine.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
A good side dish with this is rice.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix in saucepan sugar, cornstarch, milk, lemon juice, rind and oleo.
Whisk over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens. Heat slowly so it doesn't burn.
Remove from heat; cover and cool. Add sour cream.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: elegant sausage brunch
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover with croutons.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage; layer in pan.
Mix eggs, dry mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk; pour over sausage and croutons. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix soup and 1/2 cup milk, pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great with fruit and muffins.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown meat and drain off well.
In large pot, add meat and other ingredients, except beans.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer for one hour and thirty minutes.
Add beans and serve with corn bread.

title: hot gingered fruit
directions: Drain syrup from all fruit, reserving 2 tablespoons pineapple syrup.
Dry fruit well on paper towel.
Arrange fruit in 2-quart casserole with cherries on the top.
Melt margarine with ginger, stir in reserved pineapple syrup and brown sugar.
Heat until well blended and pour over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's black walnut cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Beat eggs well.
Blend margarine, shortening and sugar together with eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture, buttermilk and walnut flavoring alternately to sugar mixture.
Stir in black walnuts.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Drain salmon and remove skin and bones. In hot butter, saute onion and celery until tender.
Stir in bread cubes.
Remove from heat.

title: hot punch
directions: Dissolve red hots and sugar in water.
Cool and then add remaining ingredients.
Mixture can be refrigerated and used a little at a time.
When you get ready to mix, add 1 part of punch mixture to 3 parts water.
Heat and serve.
Makes 12 cups.

title: flan
directions: Caramelize mold.
Place 1 cup of sugar in mold.
Put directly on stove and stir constantly until melted and caramel color.
Tip pan until sides are covered.
Set aside to cool.
Caramel will harden.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops out of peppers.
Remove seeds.
Mix all ingredients and stuff peppers.
Wrap each in foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Moisten
chicken
breasts with Italian dressing. Dredge through
bread crumbs.
Place in casserole dish, prepared with Pam to prevent sticking.
Pour tomato sauce over breasts.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.	Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well, squeezing out excess liquid.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onions in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: fred harvey's cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion; cover with the 1/2 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil the 1 teaspoon sugar, salt, mustard, celery seed, peanut oil and vinegar.
Cool slightly and pour over shredded cabbage and onion.
Let stand at least 4 hours before serving.
Good for 4 to 5 days.

title: walnut chicken stir-fry
directions: Marinate chicken 15 minutes in soy sauce.
In large skillet, toast walnuts in 1 teaspoon oil over low heat 15 minutes.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil, garlic and onion for 2 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook.
Add marinade, chicken and rice to the vegetable mixture and cook 5 minutes.
Add walnuts and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain some juice from pineapple.
Pour marshmallows into whipped cream; add pineapple.
Pour Jell-O over all ingredients. Mix with a large spoon, stirring gently.
This will turn the mixture green.
Let stand overnight for best taste and results.

title: best darn salad
directions: Mix the first three ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Toss well and refrigerate.
This will keep for several days.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: german one dish casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Put browned meat and onion over cabbage.
Sprinkle rice over meat. Combine soup and water and pour over rice.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until rice is done.

title: penne in a basil meat sauce
directions: Heat olive oil and saute garlic until smell is strong, but do not burn.
Add all of remaining ingredients.
Simmer for one hour.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour.
Fry in Dutch oven in hot oil until brown.
Combine catsup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, water, salt and pepper and pour over meat.
Cover pan.
Reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour, stirring once or twice.
Add carrots and cook until done.
Serve over egg noodles and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: spicy pork loin with pineapple-papaya salsa
directions: Combine seasonings.
Rub over pork.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Unwrap pork; place on a rack in roasting pan.
Place in oven and reduce heat to 325°.
Roast 2 hours and 15 minutes or until thermometer reaches 155° to 160°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Slice and serve with the salsa.

title: zesty golden corn
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Blend in mustard.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly, over high heat until tender-crisp; about 3 minutes.
Stir in corn and pepper; beat through.
Stir in parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: praline candy
directions: Mix pudding mix, both kinds of sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Continue to cook gently, stirring frequently, until a small amount tested in cold water forms a soft ball.
Add nuts and mix well. Remove from heat and beat until mixture begins to thicken, no longer.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper and let stand until firm.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Chop the pepper, onions and cabbage (I use a blender).
To this add all the rest of the ingredients.
Cook together for 20 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 10 pints.

title: tangy italian mushrooms
directions: To marinate mushrooms, place in Italian dressing for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Drain mushrooms and saute in margarine in skillet or chafing dish for 5 minutes.
Serve warm, using either toothpicks or relish fork.
Yields 2 cups.

title: sunday brunch casserole(serves 6)
directions: Place croutons in bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Brown sausage or bacon.
Drain.
Cut into bite sized pieces and add to casserole.
Beat eggs in 2 cups of milk and pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken in water; reserve 2 cups broth.
Remove chicken from bones; cut into small pieces.
Place 2 cups of broth with soup in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
In another bowl, mix melted margarine, flour, baking powder, salt, pepper and buttermilk; mix well to form a soft dough.
Spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy cake mix
directions: Combine the sugar and cream.
Add flour and eggs; beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched lightly.
Makes three layers.
Use any kind of frosting.

title: pizza casserole(teacher's favorite)
directions: Boil pepperoni for 5 minutes in enough water to cover; drain. Saute onion in 1 1/3 tablespoons butter.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pistachio pudding mix in medium to large bowl with crushed pineapple. Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill before serving.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cold peach soup
directions: Combine nectar, juice and cinnamon in a saucepan and bring to a simmer.
Cook peaches in mixture until soft.
Puree in blender. Pour mixture into bowl.
Add cream and sour cream.
Refrigerate. Garnish with strawberries.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a baking dish.
Blender-crumb bread.
Wash and dry tomatoes; cut off tops and remove pulp. Sprinkle inside of shells with salt and pepper.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Allow cheese to soften 3 to 4 hours.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Form into logs or balls. Usually makes 8 logs.
Roll in chili powder.
May be frozen.

title: tropical trail mix
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Makes about 2 pounds.
You may want to add other tropical items if you can find them.
Some possibilities include sesame seed, Brazil nuts, dried papaya and Macadamia nuts.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sour cream. Spread on bottom of platter. Lay shredded lettuce on top of mixture.
Add tomatoes, pepper, and olives. Spread taco sauce over top. Sprinkle a package of shredded Cheddar cheese over top. Serve with taco chips.

title: mardi gras salad
directions: Put 1/3 cup water in 1 quart pan.
Bring to boil; add peas, cover and turn off heat.
Leave on burner while you chop the other vegetables.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to flour and sugar mixture, then add milk and butter.
Mix in coconut and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into two large, 4 small or 6 mini metal loaf pans, slightly greased.
Bake 1 hour at 325° until toothpick comes out clean.
Let bread cool about 5 minutes, then glaze.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Combine ingredients in mixing bowl; stir until smooth.
Set aside for 20 minutes; stir lightly.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack until ready to serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kitchen sink cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl with a wooden spoon, mix together butter, sugar, and brown sugar until smooth and creamy, about 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.

title: kid's favorite breakfast
directions: Microwave Directions:
In 1 cup microwave-safe measuring cup, combine peanut butter, milk and honey.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45
seconds or until melted and smooth, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Prepare pancakes as directed on package.
Place banana slices evenly between layers and on top of pancakes.
Pour peanut butter mixture over pancakes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: french bean basket
directions: Dissolve jello and bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add frozen beans and stir until beans separate and jello begins to thicken.
Stir in cold water, lemon juice and pimientos.
Pour into 4 or 5-cup ring mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Unmold and garnish with crisp greens, if desired.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix salad dressing, potatoes, cheese, soup, onions and pepper.
Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with corn flakes and margarine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift spices, salt and soda.
Add raisins.
Combine carrots, potatoes, shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and raisins; mix thoroughly.
Fill well oiled 1-pound coffee cans 2/3 full.
Steam 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook onion, celery and ground beef for a few minutes.
Add balance of ingredients; cook for 30 minutes, or as long as you wish in crock-pot.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice in bottom of a large buttered casserole dish. Combine cans of soup and milk.
Pour over rice. Stir slightly. Place chicken on top of rice mixture. Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind shrimp in blender or food processor.
Add onion and blend.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate.
Serve with party crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in foil with shiny side to meat.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the meat in the foil.
Wrap the meat and sauce in foil and place in 300° oven for 3 1/2 hours.
Place in refrigerator overnight and then slice.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and re-wrap meat (1 1/2 cups barbecue sauce).
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add sugar, salt, oil and the 1 cup water and mix well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Knead down every 5 minutes times 5. Divide into 2 balls and let rise 10 minutes.
Roll each ball out like a jelly roll and roll up.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cut each loaf part way down every inch.
Cover with towel and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a large heavy pan for 20 minutes. Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Beat together the sweet potatoes, sugar and butter until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk to potatoes.
Mix until soft dough is formed.
Do not overbeat.
Place dough on floured surface and roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out with a biscuit cutter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cook on wire rack.
Makes two dozen.

title: kay's strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
In small bowl combine oil, eggs and strawberries. In center of dry mixture add liquid mixture.
Stir.
Blend in nuts. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pans and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 3 minutes.
Cook rice.
Combine the hot rice, broccoli and butter together.
Mix well.
Add Cheez Whiz and mix
well.
Pour
into a casserole dish and top with almonds (optional).
Bake at 375° for at least 35 minutes.

title: glory b. cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in loaf or Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all ingredients.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.

title: sausage bake
directions: Spread sausage over rolls, then cheese.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over this.
Bake at 400° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together cream cheese, oleo and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and spread on cake while cake is hot.

title: easy chicken-n-dumplings
directions: You'll need approximately 2 quarts broth; add soup (no extra water).
Pinch each biscuit in about 4 pieces.
Drop one by one into hot, boiling broth and soup mixture; the dumplings will be bite-sized and fluffy.
Let boil on medium-high for approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Add cooked eggs and chicken.
Makes a large pot.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water together.
Cream margarine with sugar and eggs.
Add cooled oatmeal mixture alternately with flour and cocoa.
Stir in vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and mustard.
Add eggs, vinegar and jelly.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
After sauce has thickened, use beater if jelly has not dissolved completely.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and asparagus liquid.
Cook over low heat.
Add cheese and soup, stirring constantly until thick.
In a well-greased casserole dish, alternate cheese sauce, asparagus, cracker crumbs and egg slices. Top with cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake in moderate oven until well heated (about 350°) for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Have all ingredients chilled.
When ready to serve, combine in a large punch bowl.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach for five minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into a slightly greased baking dish.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Add all other ingredients and cook on low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and artichokes(yields 4 servings)
directions: Flour chicken and set aside.
Heat 1/2 stick butter in nonstick frypan until good and hot.
Add chicken and brown both sides, then cook on medium heat until done.
Dress each chicken breast with first Prosciutto, then top with Muenster cheese.
Add artichokes to pan.
Heat everything on high heat for sauteing.
Add 1/2 wine. Cook until turns into a light sauce.
Remove and serve.
Enjoy!

title: turkey and gravy
directions: Blend Dijon mustard, soy sauce and olive oil, using wire whisk.
Add juice of lemons.
Mix in fresh herbs.
Add garlic using garlic press.
Rub turkey with marinade.
Sprinkle with spike and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes per pound. After 1 1/2 hours, remove foil and baste every 15 minutes until done.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and wash peppers.
Parboil 3 minutes.
Combine rice, salt, pepper, ground beef, egg, milk and onion.
Stuff peppers lightly and place in pressure cooker on rack.
Add tomato soup and water.
Cover; set control at 10 and cook 15 minutes after control jiggles.
Reduce pressure normally for 5 minutes, then place cooker under faucet.

title: shrimp dip
directions: With mixer, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, ketchup, mustard and garlic powder.
Stir in shrimp, green onions and celery. Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first four ingredients in casserole baking dish.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: party punch
directions: Combine fruit juices, Kool-Aid and ginger ale in punch bowl. Spoon sherbet into punch.
Will serve 40 people.

title: puff pancakes
directions: Melt half the butter in each of two 8-inch pie pans.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour half in each pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Pancakes will puff up, but be soft in center.
Serve immediately with berry sauce or syrup.

title: green beans and bacon
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Add beans, brown sugar and water. Stir gently. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove to serving bowl with slotted spoon.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Place sliced chicken in casserole dish.
Salt and cover with Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and wine together.
Pour over chicken. Cover with stuffing and sprinkle with melted oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried squash
directions: Mix flour, egg and water together; salt and pepper to taste, then fry.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix together the mushroom soup, mayonnaise, chopped onion, grated cheese and beaten eggs. Combine this mixture with the broccoli.
Place in a greased casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the eggs, water and oil together.
Add to the cake and pudding mix.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5 x 2-inch) bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If using mini loaf pans, fill half full.
Let set in pans a couple of minutes before baking to get out air bubbles.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat broth to a simmer with tomato, chili, scallion and greens.
Add tortilla strips; heat through.

title: creamy caramels
directions: Combine sugar, one cup of the cream, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring constantly throughout all cooking periods.
Pour in remaining cup of cream very slowly, so that mixture does not stop boiling at any time.
Cook about 5 minutes longer.
Stir in margarine, about 1 teaspoon at a time.
Turn heat to low and cook slowly until a small amount of the mixture forms a firm ball when dropped into very cold water (248°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix gently.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes and then stir only enough to distribute nuts.
Pour into one corner of a lightly greased 8-inch square pan, letting mixture flow to its own level in the pan.
Do not scrape the cooking pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Turn the block of candy onto a cutting board.
If candy sticks, heat bottom of pan slightly.
Cool before cutting. Mark off into 3/4-inch squares and cut with a large sharp knife. Wrap each caramel in waxed paper.
Makes about 2 pounds of candy.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper in bowl.
Set aside.
Beat egg and water together.
Dip tomato slices first in egg mixture.
Dredge in cornmeal mixture to coat.
Lightly spray 10 x 15 inch baking pan with vegetable spray or spread lightly with melted butter.
Use only enough butter to keep tomatoes from sticking.
Place tomatoes in single layer in pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Turn halfway during cooking.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain green and yellow beans and corn.
Rinse and drain kidney beans.
Thinly slice carrots, celery and onion.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl with lid.
Better if made a day or several hours ahead of time.
Stir a few times to help all vegetables marinate.
Keeps for at least a week in refrigerator.

title: diet jello dessert
directions: In large bowl, place Cool Whip and pineapple.
Mix well. Sprinkle dry Jell-O over.
Place in refrigerator at least 1 hour. Any Jell-O is good. I have tried them all.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Pour into greased 13x9x2-inch baking pan.

title: oatmeal-raisin breakfast cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and pour into a small bowl to cool.
Grease a cookie sheet.

Pour oats, flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a large bowl; stir to mix well. Add sugar and egg to oleo; whisk smooth with fork or wire whisk. Pour over flour mixture and stir to mix well.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls of batter onto greased cookie sheet, leaving 2 inches between each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until cookies are lightly browned.
Let cool a minute or so, then transfer to wire racks to cool.
Makes 12 large cookies.
These are a great treat for breakfast or anytime.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and sour cream.
Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla, flour, soda and baking powder.
For topping, use mixture of chopped nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half the batter in greased pan and add half the topping.
Add rest of batter; cover with rest of topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together by hand (do not use electric mixer).
Pour into greased 8 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add fruit juice.
Mix salt and baking powder with flour.
Add cinnamon to flour.
Add.
Mix all fruit and nuts together.
Put 3 cups of flour on fruit and nuts; coat well.
Mix with the first ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture.
Grease loaf or tube pan; line pan with wax paper.
Put 4 cups water in pressure cooker.
Put cakes on rack in cooker.
Cook on 10 pounds pressure for 1 hour.
Take out.
Put in a 300° oven for 10 minutes.

title: iron skillet peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a large iron skillet.
Mix the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into skillet with butter.
Do not stir.
Drain peaches, save juice.
Pour fruit over mixture in skillet.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until golden brown.
Pour reserved peach juice over cobbler while hot.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix crust for 2 pizzas. Butter cookie sheet and spread crust onto pan. Pour pizza sauce on crust and spread out.

title: roast venison
directions: Cover roast with water; add vinegar.
Soak for 1 hour.
Rinse and dry.
Rub in margarine and pepper generously.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 3 hours and 30 minutes to 4 hours.
Do not unwrap to brown.

title: muffin biscuits
directions: Mix and put into muffin pan.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken. Debone and chop into bite size pieces. Place in buttered 9 x 13 dish. Mix soup and sour cream. Microwave briefly. Pour on top of chicken.

title: deluxe fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk in 2-quart saucepan. Bring to boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 2 minutes (rolling boil). Remove from heat; add Hershey bar, broken in pieces, Choco Bake and vanilla. Stir until chocolate melts and mix is well blended. Spread in 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm. Cut into squares. Makes 2 pounds.

title: connie's english toffee
directions: In a pan, place sugar, butter and water.
Bring to a boil of 300°.
Take off burner; add vanilla.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet or foil.
When cool, pour melted chocolate over toffee and press chopped nuts into chocolate.
Break into small pieces when chocolate has hardened.

title: venison chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides; pour off drippings.
Pour in water and soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender. Turn once or twice while baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked rice and chicken
directions: Butter a 9-inch square baking dish.
Pour about 1/4-inch instant rice on bottom. Salt and pepper.
Add a little water (not enough to cover).
Place salted chicken on top of rice.
Pour can of soup mixed with 1 can of milk over top of chicken. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: tater taco casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook meat and onion. Drain. Stir in taco seasoning and water. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Add corn and soup. Mix well. Transfer to greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange Tater Tots in single layer over the top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are crispy and golden brown. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, water and chicken.
Pour over rice in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa. Mix water and butter. Bring to boil. Add buttermilk, salt and soda. Add vanilla and cinnamon. Add eggs. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins or line with liners. Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, lemonade, oil and egg.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15-20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from tins and cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat the egg yolks and mix in the sugar and milk.
Mix in butter and raisins.
Pour into buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Beat the egg whites until frothy.
Beat in confectioners sugar and spread on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Chop corned beef in blender.
Combine all ingredients together and bake in pie plate at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on party rye.

title: dalinda's chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Good in crock-pot.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not peel cucumbers, just slice them.
Add sliced onions, chopped peppers, garlic and salt.
Cover with cracked ice; let stand 3 hours. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Heat to boiling, put in jars and seal.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell (8 or 9-inch). Bake at 425° until crust is golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onions and pepper in oil until limp.
Brown meat and drain.
Add onions, pepper and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves.
Freezes well.

title: easy candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Melt bark in a medium pan over low heat.
Blend mix into melted bark.
Pour onto buttered surface.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: mix up cake
directions: You will also need 1 large bowl.

title: sausage and biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, shredded cheese and sausage.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (20 minutes).
May be frozen and reheated in a covered pan at 325°.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook for 7 minutes.
Add chocolate; mix in marshmallow cream, stirring completely.
Add pecans.
Spread in a baking dish and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds fudge.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water in large bowl.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Chill until firm.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Roll crackers to make crumbs. Chop dates and mix with crumbs. Beat egg whites and fold in remaining ingredients with wooden spoon.
Divide into 3 (9-inch) pie tins and bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve topped with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 3 pies.

title: country ribs and kraut
directions: Mix sauerkraut and brown sugar in large shallow baking pan. Cut ribs into serving size pieces; place on top of kraut and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in slow (325°) oven for 3 hours, turning ribs occasionally to brown and crisp on both sides. Arrange on and around edge of heated serving platter; spoon kraut in middle.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, bananas, rolled oats and nuts.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoons, about 1 1/2-inches apart, onto greased cookie pans. Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry onion salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine romaine, onion and strawberries. Combine all ingredients in a small bowl or jar with a lid.
Mix well.
Pour over salad and toss.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple casserole (for ham)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve hot. Let set to firm up.

title: korean salad
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix bean sprouts, bacon and eggs. Toss like salad.
Blend oil, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, onion, catsup and vinegar a few minutes.
Pour over spinach mix and chill.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine all fruit juices.
Chill.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add carbonated beverages.
Yields 75 servings.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Pick over and wash beans and put in Presto cooker with water and salt. Pressure cook for 40 minutes according to instructions for your cooker. When pressure goes down, add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and then simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour until flavors are well blended. Adjust salt.

title: ramen breakfast
directions: Boil and mix Ramen noodles as directed on package; drain. Scramble eggs in butter.
When cooked, add noodles to skillet and stir.
Place cheese on top until melted.

title: mushroom lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Beat egg and stir in cottage cheese.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish and line with a layer of noodles.
Cover noodles with half of cottage cheese mixture.
Then layer sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy ice cream dessert
directions: Add margarine to crackers.
Put in Pyrex dish or Tupperware container.
Beat ice cream and instant pudding mix.
Bowl will be cold and have crystals on it When pudding is all mixed in ice cream, pour over cracker crumb mix.
Cover top of ice cream mixture with 1 tub of cool whip and put in refrigerator.
Chill.
It's actually ready to eat.

title: frito pie
directions: Layer Fritos and chili in baking dish.
Top with onion, tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good served with salad.

title: chicken and stove top stuffing
directions: Put chicken breast on bottom of dish.
Place cheese on top of chicken; pour cream of chicken soup, then sprinkle a layer of Stove Top stuffing.
Then pour melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and sprinkle in flour while over heat.
Add salt; set aside.
Mix spinach, cottage cheese, eggs, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Add the margarine mixture to spinach.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: eleanor's chili sauce
directions: Chop apples, tomatoes, onion, peppers and celery.
Place in a heavy-duty kettle.
Add the vinegar, brown sugar and spices and simmer 2 hours or more.
It should be thick.
Place in 6 pint canning jars and seal.

title: hot apple juice
directions: Mix all ingredients except nutmeg in a Dutch oven; simmer 20 minutes.
Remove and discard spices.

title: iced cucumber soup
directions: Heat oil and water in Dutch oven.
Saute onions and leeks until transparent.
Drain off liquid and oil; set aside.
Bring 1 cup chicken stock to boil; add cucumbers.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Drain and add cucumbers to onion mix.
Take rest of stock.
Bring to boil with potatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes, drain and add cucumbers to onion mix.
Take rest of stock, bring to boil with potatoes.
Cook until soft.
Put potato and broth in food processor and blend until smooth.
Do the same with cucumbers and onions.
Combine mixtures and chill.
Thin with skim milk.
Pour into chilled bowls and garnish with twist of cucumber.

title: white bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and shortening until warm (120° to 130°).
Shortening does not need to melt.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide into 2 parts.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix all together and put in freezer can.
You may need more or less of the soda water, depending on the size of your freezer. Get a strong arm to help turn the crank and then enjoy!

title: russian tea
directions: Use 2 rounded teaspoons per 8 ounce cup of boiling water. Makes approximately 46 servings.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Scrape, slice and boil carrots in salted water until tender. Drain and cool.
In bowl, alternate layers of carrots, peppers and onion rings.
Combine marinade ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps well.
